title: my grandmother's soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix and drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° on lower shelf until slightly browned.

title: lasagna(meat and cheese)
directions: Fry beef off with onions.
Remove fat.
Add tomatoes, paste, sugar, salt, oregano, thyme, garlic salt and bay leaf.
Heat mixture to a boil.
Stir and break up tomatoes.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Discard bay leaf and spoon off any fat on top of sauce.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed; drain well.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and preheat oven to 375°.
Lay noodles in bottom of dish overlapping each other.
In a small bowl ,mix eggs and Ricotta.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle on a layer of Mozzarella.
Spread sauce over mixture, then repeat layers.
Bake for about 45 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand for 10 minutes.

title: pudding pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir pudding mix into corn syrup in medium bowl until well blended.
Stir in evaporated milk and egg.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain.
Add 1 package of taco seasoning and let simmer for 5 minutes with 1 cup of water. Remove from heat and add sour cream.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, press refrigerated crescent rolls.
Cover with layer of crushed taco or nacho chips.
Layer shredded Mexican Velveeta cheese over chips.
Pour hamburger mixture over cheese.
Top with more cheese and crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crumbs together in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop bake
directions: In large skillet brown chops, drain on paper towel.
In 2-quart oblong pan cover bottom of dish with butter.
In baking pan arrange potatoes and mushrooms and chops.
In small bowl combine water and onion soup mix.
Pour over meat.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/4 hours until potatoes are tender.

title: delicious buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; then pour into two unbaked pie crusts. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook noodles before mixing; mix in order given.
Add a little grated cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place diced potatoes in casserole and stir all ingredients, except corn flakes, in with potatoes.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour. Put corn flakes on top about 20 minutes before casserole is done.

title: chocolate chews
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler and set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter and 1 cup sugar until creamy, then beat in eggs and melted chocolate.
In another bowl, stir together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Gradually add to the butter mixture and blend thoroughly.
Place remaining 1/4 cup sugar in a small bowl.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar to coat.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until tops appear dry.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Blend milk, juice and egg yolks.
Pour into Graham Cracker Pie Crust.
Whip egg whites with 6 tablespoons sugar, pinch of salt and a small amount of baking powder.
The baking powder will give you an extra high meringue.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix ice cream and egg in a mixer.
Add flour.
Shape rolls. Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Bring 1/2 the broth and butter to a boil.
Stir flour and remaining broth together and stir until smooth.
Pour into the boiling mixture.
Add cheese to broth and stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients (except tortilla chips) and heat.
To hold, keep over double boiler.
To serve, sprinkle with the strips of flour tortillas which have been deep-fried (they cook very quickly).
Garnish with guacamole and mixed cheese if desired. Makes 15 (8 ounce) servings, approximately.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut.
Roll into approximately 1 inch balls and roll in coconut.
(These freeze well.)

title: almond dates
directions: Toast slivered almonds in oven.
Slice dates in half.
Stuff dates with almond paste and toasted almonds.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add pumpkin, milk, molasses and eggs, beating well.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Yield: 1 1/2 dozen.

title: french-fried onion rings
directions: Peel
onions
under running water (to prevent eyes from watering).
Cut
into 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings. Heat
vegetable oil (at least 1-inch) in deep fryer or 3-quart saucepan
Beat egg and add remaining ingredients (by hand) until smooth.
Dip each ring into batter, letting excess drip back into
bowl.
Fry
a
few rings at a time in hot oil, turning once,
until golden brown, about 2 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: champagne poached peaches
directions: Combine champagne, framboise and 2/3 cup sugar in a large deep kettle and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Add peaches and poach for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and let peaches cool in the liquid, drain.
Whip the cream with the sugar and vanilla.
Spoon over peaches and serve.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add the eggs.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan, greased and floured, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Place butter in bowl and melt.
Add sugar and peanut butter; stir well.
Add 1/2 cup peanuts, then eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla and stir well.
Spoon batter into greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Microwave on High 4 minutes, turning halfway through.
Place chocolate on top, let melt, whirl.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top.
Cool, cut and serve.

title: beef stew
directions: Coat stew meat lightly with flour and brown in small amount of oil, stirring often to brown all sides.
Mix remaining ingredients in 2 cups hot water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat is tender.
Remove bay leaves.
Add diced potatoes and carrots.
Add more water if needed.
Cover and cook over medium heat until vegetables are done.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Place in casserole dish.
Peel, pit and mash avocado; mix well with lemon, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
Spread dip in bottom of casserole, then avocado mix, then sour cream mix.
Then layer in order the onions, tomatoes and olives.
Top with cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: maple sweet and sour appetizers
directions: Drain pineapple and put in saucepan the juice with the cornstarch, salt, pepper, vinegar and maple syrup.
Heat to boiling, stirring.
Add pineapple, browned sausage, cherries and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
May be cooked in crock-pot.
Serve in chafing dish.

title: linda johnson's minestrone soup
directions: Brown bacon, cook onion and celery together with garlic and basil until tender.
Stir in soups, water, tomatoes, ditalini and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Add cabbage and zucchini.
Cook 10 minutes or more.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 8 cups, 165 calories per cup.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine as listed.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 or 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked shrimp spread
directions: Blend cheese and sherry; stir in shrimp, chives and horseradish.
Stir in sour cream.
Spread in 8-inch pie plate or flan pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Spread hot mixture on crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix hamburger, onion and taco seasoning and simmer.
Combine remaining ingredients and toss together with meat.
Serve with Catalina dressing.

title: sherried beef
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 3 hours.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: powdered sugar cookies(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Sift into this the remaining dry ingredients.
Mix well; cover and chill overnight. Form 1 rounded teaspoonful of mix into ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with glass.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.
(Ovens vary; do not overcook.)
Spread on brown paper bag to cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pasta fasoli soup(low-fat)
directions: Brown turkey or beef in large pot.
Add onion and saute.
Add tomatoes, Ro-Tel, bouillon cubes, celery, carrots and seasonings; simmer 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni al dente (firm).
Add beans to soup mixture; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add pasta; allow to stand, covered, for a few minutes before serving.
A cup of water may be added to achieve correct consistency.
This is adapted from the soup served at the Olive Garden.

title: onion and garlic bread
directions: Melt butter in a small pan over moderate heat.
Add onion, garlic and season with sugar, thyme and pepper.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until onions are golden in color and translucent.
Place the split bread on a baking sheet and broil until golden.
Spread half the onion and garlic in a thin layer on each half of bread.
Sprinkle each half with a handful of cheese and return to broiler for 30 seconds, or until the cheese bubbles. Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, water and Karo syrup to boil.
Add peanuts and boil to 300°.
Remove from heat and add butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Pour on sheet of buttered aluminum foil.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar; mix until creamy.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add flour gradually.
Add flavorings.
Slowly add 7-Up.
If batter is too thick, may add more 7-Up.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes (approximately).

title: sunshine salad
directions: Combine strawberry Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups hot water; stir in strawberries, pineapple and banana.
Put in large glass baking dish.
Place in refrigerator to set.
When set, spread with the sour cream.
When strawberry layer is about half set, combine lemon Jell-O with 3 cups hot water.
Add nuts.
Place in refrigerator to set to soft stage.
Spread soft-set lemon Jell-O over sour cream layer and refrigerate until set.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir sugar and corn syrup together.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes. Stir peanuts into sugar.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes until light brown. Add butter and vanilla. Blend well. Microwave 1 to 2 minutes.
Peanuts will be lightly brown and hot.
Add soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: chicken lynn
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Cool slightly.
Then pull meat off bone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with chicken pieces.
Mix sour cream with undiluted chicken soup and spread over chicken.
The soup is salty enough, but if desired, some salt and pepper may be used over the chicken before adding the sour cream and soup.
Crush crackers and spread over casserole.
Melt oleo and put over crackers.
Sprinkle poppy seed over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Heat pan.
Add oil and fry onions until brown.
Add cold rice and saute.
Add eggs, seasoned with soy sauce and salt.
Saute until done.

title: cucumber roll
directions: Place cucumbers in water with 1 tablespoon salt.
Let stand about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Holding each cucumber piece upright and using a sharp knife, cut 1/8-inch thick around full length spirally to center.
Discard center.
Dry well.
Mix the crab meat, egg yolks, mayonnaise and 1 teaspoon salt.
Spread crab mixture on cucumber piece unrolled to lie flat.
Reroll from center to outside to form a pinwheel-type roll.
Chill very well, about 1 hour. Slice 1/2-inch thick crosswise.
Makes about 20 slices.

To serve these crab stuffed rolls as an appetizer, you may either arrange several on individual plates to eat with forks or chopsticks or place each on a thin cracker or toast round so it can be eaten with the fingers.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Combine vanilla and chocolate puddings with milk.
Beat for about
a
minute
or so.
Stir in chocolate.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into two chocolate crusts.
Chill.

title: congealed jello salad
directions: Make jello as directed on box. When jelled, with mixer, mix together jello and whipped topping, then add crushed pineapple (drained) and nuts. Let chill before serving.

title: strawberry salad mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add frozen strawberries (unthawed); add undrained pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 mixture into mold or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Leave the other half at room temperature.
Whip sour cream, cream cheese and mayonnaise together; spread over firm gelatin in pan.
Top with remaining half of gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12.

title: spice tea
directions: Insulated bottles can be kept fresh during winter storage by placing a piece of charcoal inside.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice and undiluted soups in a casserole dish. Place chicken parts dipped in melted butter on top. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: quick cheddar biscuits
directions: Mix cheese with Bisquick to coat.
Add egg to milk and beat until combined.
Add to dry mix.
Stir only until well mixed. Drop from spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Makes 12 to 15 biscuits.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in a baking dish.
Put crushed corn flakes on top.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and sugar.
Beat in small bowl the oil, eggs and milk.
Combine 2 mixtures.
Add 1 cup grated raw apples.
Stir. Bake in greased muffin tins at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pans.
Dip each muffin in melted margarine, covering all over.
Then put in a plastic bag with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and shake.

title: artichokes stuffed(carciofi ripieni)
directions: Cut
1-inch off sharp top of artichoke.
Slice off stem and reserve.
Remove
and discard tough outer leaves.
Spread leaves and
remove fuzzy choke with a spoon.
Soak artichokes under
cold water mixed with flour and lemon juice, for 3 to 4 minutes.
This removes
any
discoloration and bitterness the artichoke
may have.
Rinse
under cold water.
Mix remaining ingredients, except
oil
and water.
Arrange mixture between artichoke
leaves and in center of choke.
When filled, place artichokes and peeled reserves stems in a deep saucepan.
Pour olive
oil
over
top
of artichokes.
Add 1 cup water to pan. Cover
pan
and
cook
over medium heat for 1 hour.
If water evaporates,
add
a
little more.
Base of artichoke should be tender
to
fork
when done. Makes 4 servings.
This is great served as a first course appetizer or after the main course.

title: pineapple scallop
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add milk, pineapple and bread cubes.
Bake in greased casserole for 45 minutes at 375°. This is good instead of potatoes with a meal.

title: best cook's rice(even non-rice lovers like this.)
directions: Place rice in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart dish and add everything else.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir after 1/2 hour.
Done when there is no liquid on top.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix cauliflower, radishes, onions and cheese.
Mix the sour cream, mayo, sugar, Hidden Valley, celery salt, salt and pepper. Combine and set 8 hours.

title: company meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except chili sauce, in large mixer bowl.
Beat at speed 1 until thoroughly blended (about 1 minute).
Shape into oval loaf; place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread chili sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Yields 8 (1/2-inch) slices.

title: potato flake cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add egg, biscuit mix, flavoring and potato flakes.
Mix well.
Pinch off a small amount of dough and roll in hands.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 325° or until slightly brown.
Take off cookie sheet immediately.
Makes 40 to 50 cookies.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with lemon juice.
Add strawberries and Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Grease 3-quart casserole.
Alternate vegetables in casserole; salt and pepper each layer.
Put hamburger on top of vegetables. Mix juice with one can tomato soup and pour top of casserole.
Cook in 350° oven for two hours.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Halve green peppers lengthwise.
Remove seeds and wash. Lightly mix ground beef, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Pile into pepper halves.
Arrange in a baking dish and pour remaining tomato sauce into dish over peppers.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat and add eggs.
Beat again. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Form into small balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in granulated sugar, then place on ungreased cookie sheet
1 1/2 inches apart.
Press down with bottom of juice glass that has been dipped in granulated sugar. Flatten slightly.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: clam cave
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Carve out center of one bread, saving top.
Cut the other into bite size pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients over low heat until smooth.
Pour into hollowed bread and cover. Wrap in foil and bake for 3 to 4 hours.
Use bite size pieces of bread for dipping.

title: italian sausage dip
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Set aside.
Chop veggies.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in crock pot.
Cook on high 2 1/2- 3 hours.
Lower to simmer.
Cook until the veggies are tender.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: In a large skillet brown meat and drain.
Add other ingredient into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain.
Layer broccoli, soup and tomatoes.
Repeat layers.
Mix cracker crumbs and oleo.
Put on top of casserole.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: reese's squares
directions: Mix butter, sugar and peanut butter well and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle over top chocolate chips and put in oven (150° to 200°) until chips are melted.
Spread chocolate evenly over top.
Refrigerate 10 minutes; cut in squares.

title: southern baked yams
directions: Combine sugar and flour; cut in oleo. Add nuts.
Arrange yams in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Broil until lightly browned.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook about 10 minutes.
Brown hamburger and onions in a small amount of fat.
Place ingredients in a large saucepan and then cook about 10 minutes.

title: pasta with italian sausage sauce
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil in a covered 5-quart pot.
Add capellini and boil for 4 minutes, or until tender but firm. Drain; toss with 1 teaspoon oil.
Cover to keep hot.

title: chicken and rice soup(greek:  avgolemomo)
directions: Boil chicken until cooked.
Remove chicken and let cool. Remove chicken from bones.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake cookie crust. Meanwhile in large bowl, beat eggs, corn syrup, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans and pour over hot crust. Spread evenly.
Bake 25 minutes or until slightly firm.
Cool and then cut into bars.
Makes about 48 bars.

title: a gingerbread recipe
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add molasses and vinegar, mixing well.
Sift together flour, soda, ginger, cinnamon and gradually add these dry ingredients to the molasses mixture and mix well.
Chill dough 3 to 4 hours.

title: chile relleno breakfast casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to eggs.
Add chiles and cheeses.
Pour into pan and bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce to 350° and bake 35 minutes or until set.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.
Great for a crowd.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles and drain. Add soup, peas and tuna.
Cook on low heat. Serve with hot bread.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick. Place strawberries in baked pie crust. Pour cooled mixture over berries. Top with whipped cream. Refrigerate.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add milk and sifted dry ingredients. Beat together well.
Pour into greased and floured (use cocoa) 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Serve with ice cream or without.
Frost, if desired.

title: white cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder and salt and sift together three times.
Cream shortening thoroughly.
Add sifted flour gradually, keeping mixture light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and flavoring, beating well after each addition.
Fold in egg whites, beaten stiff, but not dry.
Bake in greased, lined pans in moderate oven (time about 30 minutes).

title: yummy cottage cheese loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients together and bake in greased casserole for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken bisque soup
directions: Add 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Stir constantly.
Add a few drops food coloring.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: rice and mushroom bake
directions: Place all ingredients in a 9 x 12-inch dish, except butter. Stir well, then cut up butter and drop around in dish.
Cover. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: berries in a cloud
directions: Lemon Mousse:
In saucepan combine sugar and cornstarch; add water, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Gradually stir hot mixture into egg yolks; return to saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly, then cover and chill.
Beat 1 cup whipping cream to soft peaks, fold 1/2 cup into lemon mixture.
Fold lemon mixture into remaining cream.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Butter a 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Place peaches on bottom. Sprinkle with lemon juice and almond extract. Sift together dry ingredients. Add egg and mix with fork or hands until crumbly. Sprinkle over peaches. Drizzle with melted margarine. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meringue cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Sift together flour and baking powder.
Alternate flour and milk when adding to butter-sugar-milk mixture.
Add vanilla.
This makes a thick batter, which should be spread thinly over two 9-inch cake pans.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Pour boiling water over berries; let set 3 to 5 minutes. Drain in colander.
Put in pan; add 4 cups of sugar.
Bring to a hard boil.
Pull off of heat for 3 minutes.
Add 4 cups of sugar; boil 3 more minutes.
Remove from heat; let set 3 minutes.
Put back on heat and boil 10 minutes.
Skim and pour in dishes.
Let stand overnight.
Put in jars, cold, and seal.

title: pineapple heaven
directions: Mix cake according to box.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Before cake is done, mix sugar and pineapple.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
When cake is done, pour mixture over cake while both are hot.
Cool cake completely.
Mix pudding by box directions and spread over cake.
Cover with whipped topping and add coconut and nuts on top.
Refrigerate.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add beef, cheese, soup, milk and onion.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy garlic dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 1 cup of lower calorie, lower fat dressing; 12 calories per tablespoon and 1 gram total fat.

title: stony gap slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in covered containers in refrigerator.
It is best to wait three days before using.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt chocolate and butter together over low heat.
Combine eggs, sugar, syrup and chocolate mixture and mix thoroughly, using rotary beater.
Stir in pecan halves.

title: warren lee's cookies
directions: Roll
crescent	rolls thin on cookie sheet.
Pour Eagle Brand milk
over	this,
then
coconut pecan icing mix.
Melt oleo. Pour on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: nut pie
directions: Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: matzo meat pie
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons oil until golden.
Add meat and spices.
Stir and cook until browned, but moist (8 to 10 minutes). Add raisins.
In small pan, saute nuts in 1 tablespoon oil.
Place stock in small rectangular dish.
Soak matzo to absorb liquid, 1 at a time.
Press 2 or 3 soaked matzo into 9-inch pie plate, cutting it where necessary to fit.
Place fillings on top.
Cover with remaining matzo.
Brush top with egg and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden on top.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: hidden treasure
directions: Lay chops in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and 1 cup onion.
Spread rice over chops.
Cover with tomatoes, remaining onion, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ranch dip
directions: Soften Cream Cheese, and add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: milky way salad
directions: Dice the apples and bananas.
Cut the candy bars into small pieces.
Use large bowl to mix all ingredients with the cup of Cool Whip.
Chill for 10 minutes.

title: apple-raisin shortcakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a small bowl, mix sugar and cinnamon and set aside.

title: b. l. t. dip
directions: Cook bacon and let it cool.
Toast bread and cut into squares. Mix all ingredients together and add crumbled bacon.
Use bread for dipping.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook the onion in shortening about 10 minutes. Stir in flour and blend. Add water and other ingredients. Bring to a boil, then simmer 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Place sugar and whipped cream in a 5-quart glass casserole bowl. Microwave for 13 minutes.
Remove and add nuts and butter. Mix together, then drop on buttered aluminum foil or waxed paper. You have to work quickly since the mixture becomes firm very fast.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine cooked rice, milk, brown sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave at Medium for 13 to 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve warm or cold topped with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add potato chips and pecans. Stir in flour.
Form into balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet. Grease bottom of glass and dip it in sugar and use to flatten cookies. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: banana sailboats
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Line individual serving dishes with vanilla wafers.
Slice bananas over wafers.
Spoon cooled pudding over this.
Decorate with marshmallows and additional banana slices, if desired.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Smash in graham cracker crumbs.
Add Chocolate Chips.
Next add Walnuts then Coconut. Finally pour the Sweetened milk over the top.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions, then add bananas, pineapple, miniature marshmallows and nuts (if desired).
When chilled, take the pineapple juice and egg egg, then sugar and flour; cook until thick. Then add the cream cheese; mix well. Spread this mixture on top of Jell-O mixture.
When cool, add Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Enjoy!!!

title: cantaberry boats
directions: Thaw the berries, if frozen.
If using fresh strawberries, remove the stems and caps; cut into halves.
Halve and seed the cantaloupe.
Spoon half of the berries into the center of each cantaloupe half.
Set aside.

title: golden cabbage
directions: Mix and place in crock.

title: mocha brownie trifle
directions: Bake brownies and cut into 1 inch squares.
Combine 2 boxes of pudding with 1 3/4 c. milk.
Stir until thick.
Add coffee mixture OR peanut butter mixture and stir.
Then fold in cool whip.

title: creamy white chili
directions: In a large sauce pan, saute chicken, onion and garlic powder in oil until chicken is no longer pink. Add beans, broth, chiles and seasonings. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 30 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in sour cream and whipping cream. Makes 7 servings.

title: easy party mix
directions: Pour oil over crackers; mix well.
Sprinkle other ingredients over crackers; mix thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(refrigerator)
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 minute.
Take off stove and add next 4 ingredients.
Mix and drop on wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Prepare noodles; drain.
Brown ground beef and chopped onion. Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce.
Mix and cook mixture over medium heat until it begins to thicken.
In a saucepan, heat evaporated milk and cream cheese until smooth. Remove from heat and stir in cooked noodles and garlic salt.

title: ooie-gooie cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on the box; let cool. Poke holes with end of wooden spoon in the cake. Spoon on caramel and condensed milk. Top with Cool Whip. Crumble up Butterfinger and sprinkle on top.

title: steak with mushroom topping
directions: Cut edges of steak to prevent curling.
Place steak on rack in broiling pan.
Put in broiler so top of steak is about 5 to 6-inches from heat.
For medium doneness, broil steak about 10 minutes on each side.
During the last 5 minutes, spread topping on steak.
Continue broiling until cheese melts, approximately 3 to 5 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, butter and sugar.
Add flour and milk, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each. Add baking powder, salt and lemon; mix well.
Pour into a tube or Bundt pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: teriyaki
directions: Cut up sirloin tips to a desired size.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Store in covered bowl or meat marinator in refrigerator at least 5 hours.
Stir a few times during marinating time.

title: hungarian chicken paprikas
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Heat butter in a large skillet and saute onion until soft and light yellow.
Lay chicken pieces over onion and saute.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 45 minutes. When chicken is tender, remove and keep warm.
Stir flour and salt into onion.
Gradually stir in chicken stock.
Stir over low heat and mix paprika into liquid.
Amount depends on taste and color desired.
Blend in sour cream.
Add chicken to sauce.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Reheat, but do not boil.
Serve with noodles or dumplings.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken to 1/4 inch thickness.
Season chicken with half of pepper and salt.
Combine rice, tomato, cheese, bran, basil and remaining pepper.
Spoon rice mixture on top of chicken breasts; fold over and secure with toothpicks.
Coat skillet with Pam.
Cook stuffed chicken breasts 1 minute on each side until brown. Transfer to shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: coconut crisps(cookies)
directions: Cream margarine with sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Stir in corn flakes, coconut and chopped nuts.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: jalepeno dip
directions: Cut cheese up in small chunks. Melt in thick saucepan over low heat stirring constantly as cheese will burn easily.
When cheese is melted, add mayonnaise stirring constantly.
Add finely chopped peppers and onions, stirring until cheese bubbles. Turn off heat, let cool and place in container.

title: spanish style pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops on a baking dish.
Place 1 tablespoon uncooked rice on each pork chop.
On the rice lay 1/2 of a small onion.
Pour canned tomato soup over the pork chops.
Cover closely and bake at 350° until done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Place half of peas in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, spread with half can of soup.
Sprinkle half of pimiento over soup.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add onion rings; bake 5 minutes longer or until onion rings are heated.
Serve hot.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tangy sauce for fruit
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; blend 1 minute.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Yields 1 cup.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Place vanilla wafers on bottom of cupcake liners.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes then top with topping, i.e., cherry pie filling or blueberry.

title: sea scallops baked in spinach leaves
directions: In small saucepan, combine chicken stock, lemon juice, thyme and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes; set aside.
In cup, combine mayonnaise and mustard.
Place a drop of mixture on each scallop.
Top with pimento strip.
Wrap each scallop in spinach leaf, folding edges under and place in shallow baking dish.
Pour liquid stock mixture over scallops and bake, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: low-fat chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, margarine, vanilla and egg white in large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chips and nuts (optional).
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown at 375°.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Mix margarine, eggs and Parmesan cheese into hot spaghetti.
In a buttered pie plate, shape spaghetti into a crust.
Brown beef; add green pepper, mushrooms and onion and cook 5 minutes.
Drain fat.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, sugar, garlic salt and oregano.
Mix together and heat for a few minutes longer.
Cover spaghetti crust with cottage cheese and spoon in meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda, sugar and cinnamon together and set aside.
Beat eggs thoroughly in mixing bowl.
Add sour cream and beat again.
Add dry ingredients and mix until just moistened.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: filled cookies(this recipe can be doubled.)
directions: Note:
This cookie keeps well in a sealed container in the refrigerator, not that the family will let them last that long.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Combine ingredients in ice cream maker. Let run 5 minutes. Add ice and salt and freeze.

title: sweet and sour hamburger patties
directions: Combine meat with salt and pepper and form into 8 small patties or balls.
Brown on all sides in hot shortening.
Mix brown sugar with vinegar, mustard and pineapple syrup and pour over meat.
Arrange drained pineapple chunks or tidbits over meat. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into baking dish.
Sprinkle with crushed corn flakes.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: swedish cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl.
Stir well.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool frosting and then refrigerate.

title: lemon snaps
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Beat eggs well and add with the milk and lemon extract.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add.
Chill. Roll 1/8 inch thick.
Cut and brush tops with egg diluted with milk.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp and brown gravy
directions: This recipe can only be successful with an electric stove.

title: icebox muffins
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over 2 cups Nabisco 100% Bran and set aside.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, buttermilk and the 100% Bran mixture.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add this to the mixture along with the Kellogg's All-Bran.
Fold only until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake as needed in greased muffin tins 2/3 full at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add corn, eggs and milk.
Saute the onions, garlic and peppers in the oil, then add to the rest of the mixture.
Pour half the mixture in pan. Sprinkle half the cheese, then add remaining mixture and cheese.
Bake in iron skillet or 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Soak oats in buttermilk.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and brown sugar.
Add to oats and buttermilk egg, margarine and blueberries.
Bake in greased pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix last 7 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over salad.

title: patti's crunchy salad
directions: Brown walnuts and noodles in butter; cool on paper towel and combine with lettuce, broccoli and onions.

title: favorite tomato soup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch round pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir dry ingredients together; set aside. In a large bowl, thoroughly cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Add alternately the dry ingredients and the soup.
Mix until smooth after each addition. If desired, 1 cup of chopped nuts or raisins may be folded into batter after the dry ingredients and soup have been added.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool thoroughly.
Frost with your favorite white frosting.

title: lunch for a bunch(dinner for a winner)
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; fold in Cheez Whiz.
Add cream soup, sliced mushrooms and drained tuna; mix all together.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
This, with a salad and biscuits, is all you need for a complete meal.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets
over
medium
heat
until
tender; cool and peel. Heat vinegar and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a rolling
boil.
Add beets and pickling spice and bring to a rolling boil.
Pack into hot jars and seal at once.

title: french toast
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs, milk, sugar and cinnamon.
Dip bread in egg mixture, coating both sides.
In a small amount of butter-margarine or cooking oil, cook over medium heat until golden brown.
Serve with syrup.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and drain lettuce and cauliflower.
Layer lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon in large bowl.
Continue to layer ending with lettuce.
Spread mayonnaise over top of last layer of lettuce. Cover and refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Before serving, mix mayonnaise and salad well.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and mix well. Sift into bowl the flour, salt and cocoa.
Alternately add flour mixture and buttermilk to creamed batter, beating well between each addition.
Then add boiling water that has had the 2 teaspoons of baking soda added to it.
The batter will be runny. Beat well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on cookie sheet; bake until brown. Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing together; spread on cooked crust.
Sprinkle with vegetables and cheese, pressing occasionally to firm.
Cut into small pieces.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed. Let cool. Drain juice from pineapple. Spoon juice in cake layers. Put icing on cake. Garnish all over with pineapple.

title: favorite chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing, margarine and water together lightly.
Put half of mixture in a
buttered
x
13-inch dish.
Mix chicken, onions, green onion tops, celery, mayonnaise and salt thoroughly and put in casserole over bread
mixture.
Top
with
remaining bread
mixture.
Beat
eggs slightly; add
milk
and pour evenly over bread/chicken mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking and spread soup over top.
Bake
uncovered
in
oven for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with grated cheese and return to oven 10 minutes.
This is the best casserole I've ever eaten!
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cinnamon-raisin muffins
directions: Mix milk, egg, margarine, sugar and cinnamon until creamy, then add dry ingredients; stir in raisins.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffins.
Remove from pan, brush tops with apple juice and roll in sugar.

title: no cook peanut butter candy
directions: Combine butter, powdered sugar and peanut butter and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with melted chocolate. Cut into squares. Chill.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients. Mix together the eggs, oil, vanilla and salt.
Pour liquid (eggs, vanilla and oil) over apple/sugar mixture. Mix well. Bake at 350°.

title: double-decker pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions and drain. Blanch green beans by cooking in pot of boiling water for 2 minutes.
Drain and rinse well with cold water.
Drain again.

title: dolly beck's glazed strawberry pie
directions: Blend flour, butter and sugar together until crumbs form. Reserve 1/4 cup mixture for topping.
Mix all together, except raisins and nuts.
Add the raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured square glass cake pan (9 x 9-inch or 10 x 10-inch); sprinkle with reserved 1/4 cup topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beet soup
directions: Barely cover carrots and beets with water, simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add butter, beef stock, cabbage and vinegar. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger.
In large pan, mix cream of chicken and Pet milk.
Cut up Velveeta cheese and add to mixture.
Cook slow until cheese is melted.
Grate Longhorn cheese and set aside.
Put hamburger meat in corn tortillas (stand like tacos).
Sprinkle chopped onions over beef.
Pour mixture over tortillas, then grated cheese.
Cook in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Put foil over pan before cooking.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Beat well.
Put in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 c. chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tea balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 300° until lightly browned, 15 or 20 minutes.
Allow to cool slightly and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg.
Place dough into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat out like crust.
Push it up on the side about an inch.
Blend all other ingredients until smooth.
Pour into center of batter.
Smooth out; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and place in refrigerator to chill.
Cut and eat.

title: french toast with pineapple sauce
directions: Place bread in a flat dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread and let stand until bread absorbs egg mixture.
Brown on warm nonstick griddle.

title: old fashion plain cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, add eggs one at a time, beating real good after each one.
Add flour with buttermilk, a little at a time, beating after each time.
Add vanilla or flavoring of your choice.
Pour into tube cake pan that has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Real good.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the herb seasoning stuffing mix.
Add sour cream last.
Pour into well-greased 6 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add herb seasoning stuffing mix.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: modeling clay(hardening type)
directions: Mix equal parts of flour and salt with enough water added to make the mixture creamy.
Do not heat.
Add a few drops of food coloring and knead thoroughly.

title: stuffed mushrooms alloette
directions: Prepare mushrooms for broiling.
Remove stems.
Fill cavity with Alloete cheese.
Broil 12-inches away from broiler unit.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients and arrange in buttered pan.

title: chicken stuffed crescents
directions: Add butter to cream cheese and mix.
Add chicken and mushrooms.
Put 1 tablespoon mixture on each roll and seal edges. Roll in butter and stuffing.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with gravy.
Yields 16.

title: pasta seafood salad
directions: Cook pasta per instructions on package for cold salad.
Mix oil, water, vinegar, Italian seasoning well.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour dressing over the ingredients.
Mix well. Chill 4 hours.

title: easy crawfish jambalaya
directions: Rinse and drain rice.
In dutch oven, saute onions, pepper, and parsley.
Add mushrooms, crawfish, all soups, tomatoes, and 1/2 can of water (or less).
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in rice. Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir lightly after 15 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top about 10 minutes before done.

title: five hour stew
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Place meat and vegetables in a casserole dish and pour the V-8 mixture over them.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes in an iron skillet.

title: mexican salad
directions: Season and salt the ground meat.
Saute in skillet until brown.
Mix all ingredients.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with green beans.
Mix soup with 3/4 can of milk. Pour over mixture.
Layer Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° until Tater Tots are brown (15 to 20 minutes).
Can use any can of vegetables with your favorite cream soup.

title: john y. brown pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar, then add melted butter; blend well.
Stir in eggs, chips, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
The pie may wiggle, but it sets as it cools.

title: hot cheese and green olive appetizers
directions: Blend cheese with butter; stir in flour, salt and paprika. Mix well.
Drain olives well.
Wrap about 1 teaspoon of mixture around olive.

title: congealed tuna
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar. Beat in egg and sorghum. Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices.
Combine with creamed mixture.
Drop heaping teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until set and slightly brown.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Debone and cut chicken into serving pieces.
Remove skin, wash and drain.
Mix Bisquick, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dip chicken into mixture and place into large baking dish in which the butter has been melted.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn over and bake for 15 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and shortening.
Beat 1 minute.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients. Roll out and cut in shapes. Bake at 325° until lightly brown.

title: spaghetti a la me
directions: Melt margarine.
Brown onion and hamburger.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: garden chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir well.
Combine chicken, 1/2 cup soup mixture, broccoli, pepper, green onions and 1 cup cheese in a large bowl.
Stir well.

title: shrimp and pasta(serves 4)
directions: Heat the butter in a medium pan.
Add shrimp, parsley and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Deglaze pan with wine over low heat.
Add fettucine and shrimp; stir.
Add half and half.
Toss in cheese, then serve.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix well and bake in unbaked pie shell for 35 minutes.

title: mexican hot dish
directions: Fry meat and onions; drain.
Mix soup, taco sauce, hot sauce and milk.
Add to meat.
In a large casserole place broken pieces of tortillas, layer of meat, layer of cheese; continue layers in this order, ending with a layer of cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: thumbprints
directions: Mix butter, shortening, egg yolks and vanilla.
Work in flour and salt.
Shape into balls.
Beat egg whites slightly.
Dip each ball into egg white; roll in nuts.
Place on sheet and press thumbprint into center.
Bake filled with jelly or tinted confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: bacon-corn cakes
directions: Cook bacon in a frying pan until crisp.
Drain and crumble. Reserve 1 tablespoon fat and discard remainder.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Stir in milk that has been mixed with vinegar.
Beat eggs and bacon grease lightly and add to the batter.
Fold in corn and reserved crumbled bacon.
Drop batter from a spoon onto a hot griddle, browning on both sides.
Keep warm until all are cooked.
Serves 8.

title: snick-o-doodle cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and 1 1/2 cups of sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Mix the dry ingredients with the shortening mixture.
Mix well. Chill dough 1 hour.
Roll out dough into balls about the size of a walnut.
Mix 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon. Roll each ball in the cinnamon mixture.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Layer cucumbers and onions with sugar in a gallon jar.
In a large saucepan, heat remaining ingredients to boiling.
Cool. Pour over cucumbers and onions in jar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: daisy cakes
directions: With sharp knife make 5 small slits evenly around each biscuit and arrange separately on cookie sheet.
Make a small indentation in center of each biscuit with fingers or a spoon.
Spoon jam in center of each.
Sprinkle on cinnamon and sugar mixture and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pizza crust and sauce
directions: Crust:
Mix yeast, 1/4 cup water and sugar until dissolves. Add salt, oil, warm water and flour; mix well.
Turn out on sprayed cookie sheet.
Work dough with oil on your hands, to cover large cookie sheet.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and chopped onion in large skillet over medium heat.
Drain off fat.
Add next 6 ingredients and simmer 10 minutes or cooked down some.
Pour 1/2 cup taco sauce into prepared casserole.
Arrange 1/2 of the tortillas to cover bottom of casserole.
Pour 1/2 cup over them.
Spoon in beef mixture.
Top with sour cream and half of the cheese.
Arrange remaining tortillas on cheese.
Spread remaining taco sauce over now and top with remaining cheese.
May be refrigerated at this point up to 24 hours.
Cover and bake 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 more minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli according to directions; drain and cool.
Mix soup, sour cream and broccoli together.
For color, stir in chopped pimento.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: mag crump's strawberry preserves
directions: Boil together water and 1 cup sugar until thick like syrup. Add 1 cup berries, cut up.
Let come to boil, cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup sugar and 1 cup berries.
Let come to boil.
Cook 10 minutes. Pour into bowl.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Fill jars and seal with paraffin.

title: super broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for crackers and butter. Pour into a well buttered 9 x 9-inch Pyrex casserole dish. Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Blend sour cream and cream cheese in a bowl. Add green chilies, olives, cheese, onion, garlic salt and jalapeno peppers. Mix well. Spread mixture evenly over each tortilla.
Roll up tightly to enclose filling. Place seam side down in dish.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Chill for several hours or until firm enough to slice. Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange on serving plate.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Melt caramels in milk in double boiler.
Mix cake as directed on package.
Put 1/2 of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour caramel mixture over first layer.
Pour rest of batter on top.
Bake for 15 minutes or until done.
Cool and frost with Dream Whip and Cool Whip.
Blend and spread on cake.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: baked ham
directions: Place pineapple rings on ham.
Combine sugar, juice and mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over ham.

title: ziti francis
directions: Fry the chicken and veal in hot oil until cooked, about 5 minutes.
Discard all the grease.
Now, add the fresh garlic and parsley and return to heat.
Stir to pick up flavors for about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add all spices; stir and add butter and let melt.
Return to low heat and add your marinara sauce and grated cheese and stir.
While all this is happening, have a pot of water on the stove ready to cook your pasta.
Cook pasta to desired softness.
Strain and add to mixture.
Heat about 1 minute while stirring.
Remove from heat and spoon onto ovensafe plate and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Place under broiler for about 1 minute; remove and enjoy.
Serves 2.

title: party rye pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients in a skillet and heat until cheese is melted.
Spread on party rye slices.
Bake at 425° until hot.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients and add with milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix altogether; put on cabbage.

title: reuben soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine the first seven ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until the cabbage and noodles are tender.
Garnish with cheese.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef in butter.
Stir in flour, onion, bouillon cube, garlic salt and paprika.
Add water and mushrooms with liquid.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Combine sour cream sauce mix with whipped evaporated milk.
Stir into meat mixture.
Add sherry and heat through.
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, butter and vanilla until fluffy. Gradually add sugars; beat just until combined. Stir in chocolate chips. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours. Place cream cheese mixture on a large piece of plastic wrap; shape into a ball. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Just before serving, roll cheese ball in pecans. Serve with graham crackers. Yield: 1 cheese ball (about 2 cups). Deliciously different!

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Add picante sauce and mushroom soup with cooked, drained rice.
Layer meat, cheese and crumbled nacho chips.
Put nachos on top and bake in 325° oven until cheese melts.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, milk, baking powder and salt.
Pour batter over oleo.
Drain cherries (reserving juice).
Scatter cherries over batter.
Pour juice over all.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over top.
Bake at 350°
for
1 hour.

title: mule pie
directions: Place sliced apples in unbaked pie shell.
Beat eggs and other ingredients; mix well and pour over sliced apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir together in large buttered casserole and bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In large pot, simmer meat in 1 quart water. Add juice, tomatoes, onions, celery and carrots. Cook until tender. Add salt, bay leaves, pepper and potatoes. Cook until tender. I add some cabbage. You may add other vegetables and more potatoes if you desire.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Fry sausage until brown and drain.
Save grease.
Mix egg and cheese.
Add sausage.
Spread dough out on a greased jelly roll pan.
Put sausage mixture in the middle.
Then, roll dough over and pinch ends together.
Pour 1/2 cup sausage grease over dough and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: five can casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, place in a baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef, soup, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and bread crumbs.
Add enough cream to hold together.
Form into small balls and bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy cheese bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir well.
Combine milk and egg; add to cheese mixture and stir 2 minutes.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool slightly.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chops. Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
You may serve over rice, if desired.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a casserole dish, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: shrimp scampi(gambino-style)
directions: Clean, devein and butterfly shrimp.
Place them in a large flat pan.
Mix all the ingredients in bowl.
Spoon over raw shrimp.
Place under broiler for 3 to 5 minutes.
Do not overcook. Spoon excess sauce over shrimp and serve.

title: macaroni fruit
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain and save 1 cup mixed juices. Save all juice from cherries.
Make up rest of cup with juice from pineapple and oranges.
In saucepan, heat juices with sugar, flour and salt.
When all dissolved and heated, add eggs and cook until thick.
Pour over macaroni and fruit and refrigerate overnight. Fold in Cool Whip and chill for several hours.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Sprinkle with salt; scatter dressing, onion soup mix and preserves over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: veggie spaghetti
directions: In a large pot, lightly brown sausage in margarine.
Remove sausage from pot, set aside.
In same pot, add cabbage, stir-fry 10 minutes; add pepper, zucchini, onion and garlic, stir-fry 5 more minutes.
Stir in sausage, chicken broth, water, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add cooked, drained spaghetti and toss. Serves 8.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt chocolate with margarine.
In large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, vanilla, sugar and slightly-colored chocolate mixture until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: lemon coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Add buttermilk and lemon rind; beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold in.
Turn into a 10-inch greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes until cake tester inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: foolproof chocolate icing
directions: Bring slowly
to
a
full rolling boil; stir constantly and boil briskly
for
two
minutes.
On a rainy or humid day, boil mixture 2
1/4 minutes.
Cool until lukewarm and add 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and beat until creamy and thick enough to spread.

title: green mango chutney
directions: Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until the fruit is tender.
Cook approximately 1 hour, stirring from time to time, to prevent fruit from burning.

title: holiday nuggets
directions: Cream shortening, butter and confectioners sugar.
Then stir in flour and salt.
Blend in vanilla, almond flavoring and chopped nuts.
Shape into small balls (one tablespoon of dough for each). Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar after baking.
Bake in slow oven at 325° about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: smoked turkey
directions: Combine Tender Quick and liquid smoke with enough water to float the
turkey
in.
Soak
the
turkey for 2 days on the breast and 1 day on the back.
Roast turkey as usual.

title: spinach or broccoli quiche
directions: Toss cheese with flour.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well. Fill crust with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: beef pot roast with gravy
directions: Wipe beef with a clean damp cloth.
Heat the suet in a heavy, deep saucepan or kettle.
Add the onion and saute until golden. Rub salt, pepper and flour into the meat.
Brown it on all sides in the fat.
Lift meat and put a rack under it.
Add the water, cover tightly and simmer for about 3 hours.
Turn the meat occasionally.
If more gravy is desired, add more water.

title: marian's klub
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix with grated potatoes.
Shape mixture into balls the size of a baseball.
Drop into a kettle of boiling water; cook for one hour.

title: stuffed pork chops(yield:  4 servings)
directions: Brown floured chops nicely.
Place in baking dish.
Melt butter.
Add onions and salt and pepper.
In bowl, pour butter mixture and beaten eggs over bread crumbs and toss to coat bread. Place 1/4 cup mixture on each chop.
Dilute soup with 1/2 can water and pour over all.
Place in 350° oven and bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes thickly.
Mix flour, corn meal, salt and pepper. Coat tomatoes with flour mixture.
Place tomatoes in hot oil. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cook on medium-high heat.
Cook quickly, just lightly browning.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pink stuff dessert
directions: Take cottage cheese and add the dry orange Jell-O.
Then add the Cool Whip to the cottage cheese.
Quick and very tasteful.

title: chicken breasts with mustard tarragon sauce
directions: Prepare the breasts by splitting in half and pounding to even thickness.
Saute breasts in butter, salt and pepper until browned and remove to a heated platter.
Add garlic to pan drippings and saute until softened.
Stir in flour, cooking until golden, then add mustard, tarragon and cream.
Simmer, stirring until the sauce is slightly thickened.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Serves 6.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Sprinkle Bundt pan with sugar (in bottom and on sides).
Mix everything together except eggs.
Beat mixture 5 minutes with a mixer, adding one egg at a time.
Pour evenly into Bundt pan. Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dieter's heavenly hash
directions: Mix all together.
Chill for about 3 hours and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turkey-mushroom quiche
directions: Arrange turkey and mushrooms in pie shell; sprinkle with cheese.
In small pan, combine soup and milk; heat until boiling, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir into eggs; pour mixture over cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and Miracle Whip until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Makes 2 cups.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to hard ball stage.
Add nuts and butter.
Cook until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and stir.
Add soda.
Stir and pour quickly onto a 10 x 15-inch (at least) cookie sheet which has been buttered.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from bone.
Cut into small pieces.
Melt margarine.
Add flour and dissolve.
Add 5 cups broth and milk.
Cook until thick.
Add celery, mushrooms, tomato paste, chopped pimentos and chopped garlic to sauce.
Let stand at least 1 hour.
(Best to let stand in refrigerator overnight.) Cook spaghetti.
Add sauce and pour into large casserole.
Cover generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with garlic bread.
Serves 20.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix as any other recipe but mix raisins, jam and nuts last.

title: nacho dip
directions: Preheat oven at 400°.
Using a fork, press the cream cheese on the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Spread the chili over top the cream cheese.
Spread cheese over top of the chili.
Put in the oven for approximately 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
It is best when served hot.
If it cools off, just put it back in the oven for a few minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Flour stew meat, salt and pepper; brown in skillet in Wesson oil. Cut up vegetables. Put all ingredients in 4-quart boiler. Add water to cover. Cook 1 hour on low heat. Mix 1 teaspoon cornstarch in water to thicken stew, if desired.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Add lemon rind and juice; mix.
Add milk and mix slightly.
Add flour, salt and baking powder; beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each addition.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: david's delicious chili with beans
directions: Cook meat until lightly browned.
Add onion.
Cook until soft. Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
This is very good reheated.
Also freezes well.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salsa together.
Spread on extra large round tray.
Add vegetables to mixture, in layers:
tomatoes, onions, green peppers and carrot.
Cover with clear plastic wrap and allow to cool about 1 hour.
Serve with taco or tortilla chips. Great for parties or covered dish affairs.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Combine rice, water and soups in bottom of roaster.
Place chicken on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover tightly.
Cook 2 hours at 350°.
Do not peek.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Cut meat into 2-inch cubes.
Combine all other ingredients, except for vegetables, and mix well.
Pour over meat; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
One hour before cooking kabobs, place the vegetables (precooked (precooked potatoes, mushrooms, cherry tomatoes and bell peppers) in with the meat.
Put on skewers; cook on grill.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar together until fluffy. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in alternately with the milk; beat until smooth.
Pour into greased loaf pan or 2-quart casserole.
Spoon drained fruit over batter.
Sprinkle sugar over fruit.
Pour fruit juice over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, ice cream, Cool Whip or milk.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Mix pudding and Jell-O in water.
Bring to boil.
Cook for 1 minute.
Pour over berries.
Mix well.
Cool and pour into shell.

title: hasty cobbler
directions: Measure and sift together the flour, sugar and baking powder. Add milk.
Mix well.
Dot an 8 x 8-inch square baking dish with the butter.
Pour mixture into the dish.
Add fruit.
Pour juice over fruit.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes or until brown on top and bubbly.

title: italian zucchini and summer squash
directions: You may peel the zucchini and squash or leave unpeeled, as you wish.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Layer zucchini, tomatoes and onion in a 2 to 3 quart Pyrex dish.
Drizzle butter over top.
Sprinkle with basil.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Remove and put Mozzarella on top; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cook another 10 minutes, until the cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: monkey ball cake
directions: Use Bundt or non-separating angel cake pan, greased.
Separate biscuits (40) and cut each into fourths.
Put 2/3 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon into large mixing bowl.
Mix together.
Coat each individual biscuit piece completely in this cinnamon and sugar.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add 1 cup sugar, bring to a boil to form syrup.
Place first prepared can of biscuits (40 quartered pieces) in bottom of greased pan.
If you wish to add chopped walnuts or pecans and raisins, do so now by sprinkling on top of first layer.
Add second can of prepared biscuits and more nuts, raisins if desired.
Pour half of boiled syrup over the second layer.
Add third and fourth cans of biscuits, alternating with more raisins and nuts.
Pour balance of syrup over last layer. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Let stand in pan for about 10 minutes and turn upside down on plate.
Pull apart as you eat.

title: pottage
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add wieners and brown.
Add all ingredients to cooked, diced potatoes and simmer about 30 minutes, then serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook beef and celery in skillet.
Brown zucchini in skillet drippings.
Alternate layers of zucchini and beef in shallow 2-quart baking dish, sprinkling with salt and pepper to taste. Stir together tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes, until zucchini is tender.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Cream soft butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Sift and add flour and salt.
Add walnuts.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 minutes in 375° oven.
Bake until set but not browned.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.
Cool and roll in the sugar again.
These store well in a covered container.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pinch 2 crescents together to make 4 rectangles.
Put 1/2 cup mixture into each rectangle.
Fold up crescents and seal edges.
Twist on top.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle bread crumbs on top, if desired.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Pour off fat, add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together.
Add other items. Stir well and pour into large flat dish.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer and cut when ready to serve.

title: cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° if using glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate morsels, coconut and nuts; press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Makes 24 bars.

title: santa's surprise punch
directions: Chill pineapple juice and 7-Up.
Pour additional 7-Up into ice cube trays, placing a maraschino cherry in each cube.
Freeze.
At serving time, combine the pineapple juice and orange juice in punch bowl.
Add peppermint extract.
Slowly pour in 7-Up.
Add ice cubes.
Makes 30 punch size cups.

title: white beans
directions: Mix all together.
Spray oven bowl with nonstick spray.
Pour in bowl and cook at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Peel apples, cut in quarters and seed.
Roll biscuits; cut in half and wrap apple quarters using 1 biscuit for 2 quarters.
Layer in dish.
You will have 20 pieces.
Put water and sugar in saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over apple dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: ground beef chop suey
directions: Brown beef
and
onions;
drain.
Pour	into large bowl with other
ingredients,
except
noodles.
Stir and mix well. Pour into baking
dish
and
bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Last 15 minutes, put noodles on top of casserole and brown noodles.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Dice fruit and chop nuts; set aside.
In very large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and blend.
Sift dry ingredients and add to fruit and nuts. Blend.
Gradually add liquids.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Turn into lined and greased pan (large tube pan).
Bake until tests done.
Place a pan of hot water on rack underneath cake during baking period.
Cool 30 minutes before removing from pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.
Makes 7 1/2 pound cake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut broccoli up into small pieces and cook until tender.
Cook rice per package directions (usually 2 cups water to 1 cup rice until water is absorbed).
Put the broccoli and rice in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Add all the other ingredients.
Stir together and bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add noodles.
Cook until tender. Drain water from noodles.
Mix remaining ingredients together with noodles.
Stir well.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: cinnamon jumble cookies
directions: Mix shortening or margarine, sugar and egg.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Chill dough.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon (1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon).
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 4 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: children's recipe for bubbles
directions: The present dining hall is significant for my husband, Galen, and me (both graduated '66).
It was in that place that we became acquainted during Junior class homeroom meetings.
We were seated alphabetically -- Lehman - Longenecker - and we became friends quickly.
We were married in 1967.

title: chicken in dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a

13 x 9-inch baking pan that has been sprayed with vegetable cooking spray, pour in mixture. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife that has been inserted comes out clean. Remove from oven and allow to stand for 10 minutes. Serve immediately. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth. Spread mixture on small serving plate (may top with chopped peanuts).
Serve with apple wedges.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and flour until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add strawberry jello and food coloring.
Pour over strawberries in baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: easy cream cheese dip
directions: (Can add a little sour cream or milk so that it won't be so stiff.)

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar.
Beat well.
Now, add granulated sugar and mix until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each 3 minutes.
Add milk and vanilla and mix.
Mix nuts.
Save 1/2 cup.
Add flour before adding nuts. Bake in pan for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.
Line pan in wax paper.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until done; debone and place in bottom of pan or dish (Pyrex, 13 x 9-inch).
Mix soup and Veg-All.
Heat.
Pour over cut up chicken.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter a 26 - 28 inch piece heavy duty aluminum foil.
In a large sauce pan, combine sugar, syrup and water.
Bring to a boil (238 degrees) and add peanuts.
Stir until brittle stage (300 -305 degrees).
Turn off heat.
Add butter and stir.
Add vanilla and stir.
Add baking soda and stir quickly and pour onto foil --- spread very thinly.
Allow to cool and break into pieces.

title: pinakbet ilocano
directions: Wash and clean ampalaya and eggplant and quarter-slice them. Chop the tomatoes coarsely. Place the slice of pork

at the bottom of a medium size pot. Add the rest of the ingredients and add 1 1/2 cups water. Bring to a boil. Add fish sauce and reduce heat to simmer. Cover and cook until vegetables are tender and flavor has blended. Season with black pepper. Stir and serve hot. Serves 4 to 6.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Slice carrots and place in 1 quart baking dish with butter and brown sugar.
Cover tightly and microcook for 9 to 11 minutes. Stir after 5 minutes.
Mix water and cornstarch until smooth and stir into carrot mixture.
Add pecans.
Cover and microcook for about 3 minutes or until thickened.
Stir before serving.
Can use canned carrots. Be sure to drain, always vent.

title: oven fried zucchini spears
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Spray nonstick cookie sheet liberally or wipe lightly with vegetable oil.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper on a sheet of wax paper.
Quarter the zucchini lengthwise, then slice each spear in half or thirds to make shorter spear.
Place them in plastic bag.
Add oil and water.
Close bag and shake so spears are lightly coated with oil. Roll each spear in crumb mixture until lightly coated.
Arrange spears in a single layer on pan.
Bake uncovered in hot oven for 7 minutes or until spears browned and tender and crunchy.

title: pint-size heros
directions: On cutting board, use sharp knife to cut tomato into thin slices.
Use table knife to spread mayonnaise or salad dressing and mustard inside buns, if you like.
Tear lettuce leaves to fit the buns.
Stack everything that you want on the buns.
Makes 4 buns.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and mix with egg mixture.
Add zucchini, nuts, raisins and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring 6 cups of sugar and 4 cups of water to a boil; let cool in a large container.
Mix remaining juices, containers of water and mashed bananas.
Add mixtures together.
Freeze in quart cartons.
Three to four hours before use, take out of freezer and refrigerate.
Mix with ginger ale in punch bowl.
Has slushy texture.
Serves about 48 (2 punch bowls).

title: grandmommy q's scrapple
directions: Don't get meat too lean.
Cook in 2 quarts water; cook liver less time.
When tender, put through a meat grinder and add 4 more quarts water.
Add corn meal, salt and pepper.
Simmer for about an hour, stirring every few minutes.
Pour into wax paper lined small bread pans.
Cool and freeze or slice 1/2-inch thick and fry on each side until crispy.
Serve with chili sauce.

title: blueberry or cranberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Make a well into the center. Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients. Stir quickly, just until dry ingredients are blended.
Gently stir in blueberries or cranberries.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Gently boil water and zucchini for 6 minutes.
Add drained pineapple, lemon juice and sugar; boil for 6 more minutes.
Add jello and Sure Jell; bring to a rolling boil for 2 minutes.
Seal in jar or put wax on them.

title: candy
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, except for the chocolate chips and the wax.
Roll into little balls.
Melt the chocolate chips and the wax in a double boiler.
Take the rolled balls, one at a time, and roll in the melted chocolate.
Put onto wax paper to cool.
