title: cauliflower-broccoli hot dish
directions: Thaw veggies and place in baking dish.
Heat soups and Cheez Whiz together.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake about 55 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle fried onion rings on top and bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, once with soda and salt.
Cream shortening, sugar and brown sugar together.
Add beaten eggs and mix until smooth; add peanut butter and vanilla and stir well.
Add flour mixture and mix into a stiff batter.

title: summer cooler
directions: Mix in blender until ice is crushed.

title: spicy carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Cream sugar and oil, beat in egg yolks one at a time beating well after each addition.
Beat in hot water.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices. Stir in carrots, pecans and egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove.
Make glaze with 1 cup powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Dribble over cake.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Stir and mix well.
Place in a flat type dish and cover with sharp grated cheese. Don't use a casserole, the flat type pan is better so the potatoes will be crunchy (10 x 15-inch pan).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish. Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet until beef is browned and onion is tender. Stir in catsup, Worcestershire sauce and 2 tablespoons baking mix.
Mix well and set aside.

title: hamburg-rice casserole
directions: Cook fat, hamburg and onion for about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes in greased casserole dish.
Remove from oven and add 1/2 can chow mein noodles and bake 10 minutes more.

title: beef a la stroganoff
directions: Cut steak in 3/4-inch pieces.
Dip meat in flour, brown in fat, add onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Cook a few minutes, then add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice cooked in consomme soup.
Also good served over noodles.

title: out of this world salad
directions: Spread mayo over top of salad.
Cover mayo with grated cheese. Sprinkle bacon bits on top and enjoy.

title: crock pot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in crock pot and cook on low for 4-5 hours.
It should be firm when you touch the center. Serve warm with ice cream or cool whip.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Place in greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ham and egg brunch
directions: Cut bread into cubes.
Toss bread cubes and ham cubes in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Distribute evenly.
Sprinkle cheese cubes, green pepper and mushrooms over mixture.
Beat eggs until foamy; beat in milk, dry mustard and salt.
Pour evenly over bread mixture.
Pour melted butter over top.
Cover tightly with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour. Cut in squares to serve.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pile into two 9-inch pie crusts. Freeze until firm.
Soften a short time before serving.

title: sweet, sour beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and set aside (crumble). Separate onions in rings.
Cook in bacon drippings until tender. Stir in sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar.
Simmer 20 minutes; drain all beans.
Combine with onion mixture and bacon pieces.
Put in bean pot or casserole; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes into a 13 x 9-inch pan, salt and pepper.
Place seasoned pork chops on top.
Pour soup on top, then milk.
Bake at 350° until cooking (about 1 1/2 hours), then 400° until done (about another 1/2 hour).

title: chicken and pasta
directions: Cook pasta and set aside. Heat oil over low heat. Add chicken, onions and pepper. Cook until chicken is no longer pink and vegetables are tender. Stir in soup to which water has been added, then pasta and mixed vegetables. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pickles
directions: Peel cucumbers; soak in salt brine overnight, also onions. Bring vinegar, water, mustard seed and sugar to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Boil about 3 minutes.
Put in jars and seal at once.
Add turmeric if you want it yellow.
Can also add a little alum if you like.
This recipe was from Erma Gass.
Yellow cucumbers would be best.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop batter by tablespoon into hot oil (1/2 inch).
Fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: tapioca fruit pudding
directions: Dissolve pudding mix in 3 cups juice (drained and saved from fruit).
Bring slowly to boil until clear.
Refrigerate until cool.
Add fruit.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: capt. steve's spicy meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Roll in 1/4 cup of seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake in oven at 375° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cranberry walnut spinach salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients. Add Italian dressing as desired for taste.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter and mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients with electric blender until smooth.
Pour into small glasses.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve immediately.
Makes 5 cups.

title: super summer salad
directions: Put broccoli, carrots and beans into a steamer basket.
Place steamer basket in a pot with about an inch of water in the bottom and cook on medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Add red and green peppers to vegetables.
Cook macaroni like directions say on box; drain well.
Toss vegetables and macaroni.
Mix oil, vinegar, oregano, basil, dry mustard and pepper together.
Add vegetables and stir.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix Jell-O in boiling water; set aside to cool.
Combine cake mix in large bowl with remaining ingredients including cooled Jell-O.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan (Bundt pan) and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: frittata
directions: Cook the zucchini, green onions and garlic in olive oil and margarine until the zucchini is tender.
Add the mushrooms, crumbled bacon and the tomato.
Stir in the eggs.
As they cook, add the cheese and the sauce.
Pass the extra Bearnaise sauce around.
Serve with a green salad and garlic bread.

title: sue's pork chops in wine
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt, pepper, garlic powder and thyme. Brown on both sides.
Put into 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish. Mix together cream of celery soup, white wine and mushrooms with liquid.
Pour this sauce over the chops.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: cutout cookies
directions: In large bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Cut margarine and shortening into flour mixture (using a pastry blender).
In a small bowl, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla. Pour egg mixture over flour mixture; mix well.
Chill.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick and cut into shapes using cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Drain the pineapple and save the juice.
Cut up the bananas and add bananas, pineapple and marshmallows to jello mixture.
Chill until set.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend milk and egg yolks; add sugar and cornstarch mixture.
Cook over medium heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, butter and coconut.
Let cool, stirring occasionally.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Top with meringue; sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator until serving time.
Keeps well for weeks.
Boil shrimp in a large pot with 1 lemon slice, 1 can beer and 1 tablespoon seafood seasoning for 8 minutes.
Drain in colander.
Serve with sauce.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except paraffin and chocolate chips; roll into small balls.
Simmer paraffin and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Roll balls in chocolate-paraffin and put on wax paper.

title: turkey chili
directions: Heat oil.
Add onions, garlic and celery; cook until tender. Add turkey; cook until pinkness is gone.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder and cumin.
Simmer for 29 minutes.
Mix in beans, salt and pepper.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Grease three 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Fill each 1/3 full.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil whole potatoes in their jacket, cool and peel.
Dice into large bowl.
Dice the eggs, saving one for garnish, and combine with the rest of the ingredients in a separate bowl.
Pour the dressing over the potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Slice the reserved hard-boiled egg and arrange the slices on top.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours to allow the flavors to develop. Serve cold.

title: glenda's soup
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 2 to 3 hours.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill for several hours.
Drop by spoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and cream; boil to soft ball.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; beat until candy begins to cake.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Cut rhubarb and put in pie shell.
Mix sugar, flour and nutmeg and add beaten eggs to it.
Pour mixture over rhubarb.
Cover edges of pie shell with foil and bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Take foil off and bake 20 minutes; remove from oven and cool.

title: sausage and egg bake
directions: Cook sausage thoroughly and drain.
Place bread cubes in casserole.
Top with cooked sausage and grated cheese.
Mix eggs and milk together with seasoning.
Pour over layered ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Place in oven at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: elouise's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to soft ball stage (234° to 245°). Add peanuts.
Continue
cooking
to
hard	crack stage (300° to 310°).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and soda.
Mix well.
Pour onto greased
baking
sheet
spreading
as thin as possible. Using greased
rubber gloves to protect hands, pull and stretch until very thin.
Break into pieces.

title: hobo supper
directions: Pat ground beef into 3 hamburger steaks.
Cut up potatoes and carrots.
Slice onions.
Wrap ground beef, potatoes, carrots and onions in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: In a large stockpot, bring water, 2 tablespoons oil and salt to a boil over high heat.
Stir in spaghetti and cook 10 to 12 minutes or until tender. Drain and rinse with cold water; set aside.

title: grilled ham and cheese
directions: Spread margarine on each slice of bread.
Lay 4 slices of the bread, buttered side down, in a skillet or on a griddle.
Lay a slice of cheese on top of the unbuttered side, followed by the slice of ham on each of the 4 slices of bread.
Take the remaining 4 slices of buttered bread and cover the sandwiches with the buttered side up.
Turn stove on medium heat and brown sandwich on bottom, then using spatula, flip sandwich over and brown, being careful not to burn.
Serve with pickle chips.

title: tomato relish
directions: Pour boiling water over green tomatoes and let stand for 5 minutes.
Mix sugar and vinegar and other ingredients.
Boil until tender. Pack in jars and seal.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine caramels, butter and milk in heavy medium saucepan.
Stir over medium-low heat until caramels melt and mixture is smooth, about 6 minutes.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour half the batter into prepared pan.
Bake until top appears dry and cake is almost done, about 15 minutes.
Pour caramel mixture evenly over cake.
Sprinkle 1 cup pecans and chocolate chips over caramels.
Pour remaining batter over filling.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans. Bake until toothpick inserted into top half of cake comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool cake completely.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in pan, stirring, until boiling.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix until all are coated.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce and salt.
Take 1/3 of sauce mixture and put on bottom.
Add noodles and spread 1/2 of Ricotta cheese.
Put 1 cup Mozzarella cheese on top of Ricotta and repeat 1 time.
Add meat sauce on top of Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and cook at 325° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and put last of Mozzarella and 1/2 Parmesan cheese and let set until melted.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Allow broccoli to thaw.
Melt margarine.
In a large bowl, combine cornbread mix, onion and salt to taste.
Add cottage cheese, butter and eggs.
Add thawed broccoli.
Pour into 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until well done.

title: granola *
directions: Heat oil, honey and vanilla.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix.
Spread on oiled cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, stirring at 5 minutes, then 4 minutes, then 3 minutes and 3 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Drain pineapple.
Save syrup. Add enough water to syrup to make 3/4 cup, then add to gelatin. Add cranberry sauce and put in refrigerator to set.
Add celery or nuts and put back in refrigerator to set until firm.

title: hearty bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown
ground beef and onion; drain.
Cook bacon and drain off fat.
Add all ingredients together; mix well.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix Crisco and 3/4 cup sugar, then add egg.
Sift together cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix all together and roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Then roll in 2 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place on cookie sheet.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.

title: smothered steak (crockpot meal)
directions: Place steak strips, flour salt and pepper in crockpot. Stir well to coat steak. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook on high for 1 hour. Then turn to low for 8 hours or high for 5 hours. Serve with rice.

title: kahlua(fabulous)
directions: Boil, then simmer for 1 hour covered.
Cool.
Add 1 fifth vodka.
Pour in clean, corked bottle.
Store for 3 weeks in a cool, dark place.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, then the meal and juice. Bake in a pie crust at 325°.

title: chili con carne
directions: Crumble meat into a 3-quart casserole.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap and microwave on High for 6 to 9 minutes, breaking up meat and stirring after 4 minutes, until meat is no longer pink.
Drain and rinse meat mixture to remove fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and microwave 12 to 18 minutes.
Stir every 6 minutes until boiling.

title: noodles a la king
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, melt butter and cook onion until tender but not brown.
Stir in soup, milk and remaining ingredients; bring to a boil and then simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes or until heated through.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.
Serves 6.

title: sugar gem cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter, oil, eggs and vanilla until light.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture and mix well. Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with a glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: wacky chocolate cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; beat in eggs.
Stir in sauerkraut and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt.
With a wooden spoon gradually work into sauerkraut mixture. Drop by level teaspoonfuls, about 1 1/2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
At once, remove with wide spatula to wire rack to cool.
If desired, cover with chocolate frosting. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: white chocolate pecan cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar and margarine until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, soda and salt, then gradually blend into butter mixture. Stir in pecans and vanilla chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool slightly, then remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: tourtiere
directions: Cook meat, onions and spices, covered with water for 1 hour, simmering.
Boil potatoes separately.
Break up, mix with meat. Makes enough for 2 pies.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place the chicken in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place sauerkraut over the chicken.
Top with the Swiss cheese slices.
Pour the Thousand Island dressing evenly over the cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease. Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Blend and toss.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: winter's best gingersnaps
directions: Mix together margarine and shortening.
Work in 2 cups sugar. Cream all together until light.
Beat in eggs and molasses.
Stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and ginger.
Beat flour mixture into creamed mixture.
Beat hard; mixture will be soft.
Chill dough for at least 1 hour.

title: carne desebrada(shredded meat)
directions: Place meat in pot and cover with water.
Boil until tender. Save liquid.
When cool, shred meat and place in pot with 1 1/2 cups of leftover liquid.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer approximately 35 minutes.
Meat may be served with side dishes or wrapped in corn or flour tortillas.

title: mincemeat cookies(about 1890, from my mother's cookbook)
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and mix.
Add egg, slightly beaten, and seasonings.
Beat together until blended.
Sift dry ingredients together; add mincemeat and nuts alternately with milk to first mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto an oiled cookie sheet leaving an inch or so between cookies.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields about 2 1/2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake in a casserole dish sprayed with Pam at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers, e.g., Triscuits, Wheat Thins, etc.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except nuts) and form mixture into a ball.
Roll ball in nuts to coat.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy fudge cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa. Add beaten eggs, buttermilk, oil, hot water and vanilla.
Mix by hand; mix well.
Pour into prepared muffin tins (use paper fillers).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: coconut chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, white sugar, brown sugar and vanilla flavoring; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate morsels, nuts and coconut.
Spread in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let cool; cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 35 squares.

title: best banana split dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crust.
Crumble all 4 shortcakes evenly on the graham cracker crust.
Beat well the butter, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla for about 10 minutes. Pour over shortcakes and crust.

title: microwave peanut brittle(be fast, use glass dish and wooden or plastic spoon)
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar and Karo syrup in glass dish; cook on High 6 minutes.
Stir after 1st three minutes.
Take out and add butter, vanilla and salt.
Cook 1 minute on High.
Take out and add 1 teaspoon baking soda and stir (beat) few seconds.
(It will change color.)
Pour on greased paper.
Break after 5 minutes. Soak utensils in hot water to clean.

title: granny patterson's chocolate custard
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, cornmeal and eggs.
Add milk, margarine and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: scotch cake
directions: Together bring butter, oil, water and cocoa to a rapid boil. Mix together flour and sugar, then add to liquid mixture and mix well.
Gradually add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla, baking soda and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool.
Cover with frosting.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Place
beans
in
bottom
of casserole dish.
Alternate layers of
cornbread
crumbs, peppers, onions and tomatoes in casserole until
all	ingredients
have
been
used.	Combine mayonnaise and pickle juice; pour over mixture.
Cover tightly and
chill	in refrigerator for several hours or overnight, if possible.
Just before
serving,
crumble the crisp bacon and sprinkle on top. Serves 8 to 10.
Yum!
Yum!

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Mix potato and sugar together.
Roll out thin, spread with peanut-butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll.

title: creamy cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese.
Cream well.
Blend in 1/3 cup coconut, the onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and chill at least 6 hours.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix beef with garlic salt and parsley; make into balls.
In a large saucepan, combine water, garlic powder, ketchup, salt, soy sauce, tomato paste, pineapple juice, vinegar, brown sugar and flour.
Cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Add meatballs; simmer for about 1 hour on low heat.
Add sliced green pepper, pineapple slices and onion.
Cook for 3 minutes.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix eggs, corn bread mix, butter and sour cream.
Add corn and bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: walnut slice cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into rolls and chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Cut in butter.
Add egg and milk.
Stir until blended.
Turn into baking sheet.
Make about 9-inch rounds.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Soak the lentils in the water for 2 hours.
Place (water included) in soup pot, and add the soup stock, potato, carrots, vinegar, salt and cloves.
No pepper!
Cook over low heat for 3 hours, and serve with sherry and Parmesan cheese in a bowl.

title: spicy doughnuts
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients, except sugar.
Set aside. Beat eggs, sugar and oil together in bowl.
Add buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients and beat smooth.
Cover and chill 1 hour. Heat oil in deep fryer to 375°.
Roll dough out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut doughnuts and fry four at a time.
These may be iced or covered with powdered sugar or eaten plain.
Delicious.

title: light pecan pie
directions: Beat 4 eggs whites with a little salt.
Fold in 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
In separate bowl, crush 23 Ritz crackers. Mix in 3/4 cup chopped pecans and 1 teaspoon baking powder.
Stir and fold into egg whites.
Place in greased pie pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced cider
directions: Simmer all ingredients together. Serve hot. Remove spices. Refrigerate any leftovers. Delicious to reheat.

title: baskin robbins pie
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, oleo and 1/2 cup chopped nuts; press into pie plate and bake 20 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: potatoes with pork chops for lisa
directions: Brown pork chops on each side, cooking for 20 minutes.

title: lep cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Put soda in butter or sour milk; add to mixture.
Add powdered alum.
Add flour in 4 parts.
Bake in fairly hot oven.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Mix cranberries, 1/4 cup sugar and pecans.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Cream butter and sugar; then add eggs and flour.
Pour over berries.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: picante brunch quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Arrange cheese, bacon, and onions in pie crust.
Mix eggs, picante sauce and half & half.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Bake 35 minutes of until crust is golden and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Serve with additional picante sauce.
Serves 6.

title: ranch baked beans
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef and onion until beef is done. Drain off fat.
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: buumer's meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk. Add eggs, meat, onions and seasonings. Mix well and form into a loaf; place in greased pan. Cover with Special Piquant Sauce.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Cook white cake as directed.
Remove cake from oven and punch holes in it with a wooden spoon.
Pour Pina Colada mix over hot cake until holes are full.
Let cake cool.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.
The longer the cake sits, the better.

title: cheese bread with a twist
directions: In mixer bowl, combine 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Heat water, milk and butter until lukewarm.
Add to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add egg to 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup flour; beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough; knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: dunk sandwiches
directions: You need 1 piece of
cube
steak
and 2 slices of bread for each sandwich.
Pan-fry
steaks
over medium heat.
Season to taste.
Drain fat from skillet. Do not scrape skillet.
Add 1 teaspoon or 1 beef
bouillon
cube
for
each
cup of water. Season to taste.
Scrape skillet.
Pour into small bowls.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	Spread half of potato slices in a 1 1/2 to 2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of seasoning and cheese.
Spread
other
half
of
potatoes over this. Combine milk and
soup and pour over all.
Sprinkle remaining seasoning and cheese
on	top.
Bake,
uncovered,
to
75 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice well. Stir in pineapple, coconut and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into baked pie shells.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight before serving.

title: jelly cake
directions: Cream the butter and margarine.
Add sugar gradually; continue beating.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add flour, bit by bit.
Add milk after each addition of flour.
Grease and flour 3 layer cake pans.
Bake in a 300° oven until browned and shrinks from sides of pan.
Remove cake from pans; place on wire racks. When cool, spread with your favorite jelly.
Spread lemon frosting on top and sides.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Take yeast and put in warm water with sugar; set aside. Measure flour, put in a bowl.
Add milk and oil with warm water and yeast.
Add to flour and mix real well.
Knead it for a few minutes and put back in a buttered bowl.
Let it rise, about 2 hours.
Then make it out in biscuits.
Let them rise and cook in oven at 375° until brown.

title: apple dumplings
directions: For Syrup: Mix 1 cup of the sugar, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and 1 3/4 cups water. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine.

title: apricot nut cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Mix all together and pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.
(If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.)

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Stir the first 5 ingredients on low heat until mixture bubbles.
In a large bowl, mix the sugar, flour and baking soda. Stir in hot mixture into dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth. Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until puffed and firm to touch in center.
After cake has cooled, spread on peanut butter (1 1/2 cups), then add on icing.

title: stand firm lasagne
directions: Prepare 1 lb. lasagna noodles as instructed on package. No-boil noodles work fine.

title: garlic roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large baking dish, toss together potatoes, oil, garlic salt and pepper.
Bake, turning several times, 1 hour or until golden.
Add parsley and lemon peel.
Toss lightly and serve.

title: scripture cake
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young. When selected
give
your
entire
thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some	wives
insist on keeping them in a pickle and others are constantly getting them in hot water.
May make them sour, and
bitter,
however.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender, and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened love,
and	seasoned
with	kisses.
Wrap in a mantle of charity and keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared they will keep for years.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain; pour in beans and sauce.
Stir.
Let cook for 5 minutes.
Add Veg-All, cover and let simmer 5 more minutes; spoon over rice and serve.

title: beef burgundy over rice
directions: Mix all together in roasting pan or similar pot.
Cover and cook 4 hours at 350°.
If not thickening by 1 hour before done, remove lid and allow to cook, uncovered, until it looks thick enough.
Cook longer than 4 hours as long as liquid doesn't cook away or get too thick.

title: shrimp pilaf
directions: Saut together the margarine, pepper and onion. Add shrimp and cook until shrimp turn pink. Add the consomm soup, water and rice. Salt and pepper to taste and cook until done.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Combine dry ingredients and add to oil mixture; mix just until moistened.
Combine oil, sugar, egg yolks and water.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed, just until combined.
Stir in sweet potatoes, pecans and vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into cake pans and bake at 350°.

title: spanish hamburg
directions: Fry meat, onions, celery, salt and pepper until meat is gray (don't brown).
Break toast into small pieces and put in a large roaster with hamburger mixture.
Pour tomato juice and catsup over all and mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes delicious hot sandwiches for a gathering.
Serves 30.

title: sauteed zucchini and carrots
directions: Cut zucchini and carrots in 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Spray a large skillet with vegetable cooking spray and place on high heat.
Add zucchini, carrot strips and red onion.
Saute 5 minutes or until vegetables are slightly soft.
Place vegetables in a serving bowl and toss with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Serves 4. Has 40 calories.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Cut up all vegetables.
Mix mayo and Hidden Valley.
Mix all together.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: cool blueberry pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with lemon juice, then add Cool Whip. Fold in rinsed and drained blueberries and nuts.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: apple red cabbage
directions: In a large saucepan or skillet, gently cook the onion in the hot margarine until golden.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook gently, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is tender. Taste and correct the sweet-sour taste.
Serve hot.
Makes about 6 servings.
Good with pork.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water until tender.
Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish in one layer to cover bottom of dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine remaining ingredients (except cheese and crumbs).
Pour over chicken; sprinkle on cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly. Serves 4 to 6 (generously).

title: crisp crusted baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Beat egg and milk in bowl.
In another bowl, put potato flakes, garlic and cheese.
Roll chicken in egg mixture, then in potato mixture.
Melt butter in shallow pan; roll chicken in butter, leave skin side up.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese finger sandwiches(1993 daisy bake-off winner)
directions: Mix all ingredients well (except bread).
Spread on white or wheat bread.
Use cookie cutter to cut different shapes (cut off crust first).

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, put large can pineapple (not drained) and cherry pie filling.
Spread out to cover pan, then sprinkle on top the yellow cake mix (dry).
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and pat down.
Dot with margarine.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Toss all ingredients together and chill.

title: hollyday mint pie
directions: Mix cookies and hot water.
Spoon into crust and gently spread to cover bottom.
Beat cream cheese until smooth and gradually beat in sugar, milk and peppermint extract.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine crab meat, celery, green onions and pimento in bowl. Sprinkle with salt and lemon juice.
Toss to mix.
Add just enough mayonnaise to moisten; mix well.
Sprinkle top with parsley.

title: wine jelly
directions: Put wine and sugar in top of double boiler over boiling water. Stir constantly until thoroughly heated.
Remove from fire.
Add Certo.
Pour in glasses and cover with Parowax.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Mix 1 1/3 cups flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cut in butter with 2 knives until crumbly.
Stir in 2 tablespoons sour cream. Turn into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or 10-inch quiche.
Pat evenly, making crust.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: michigan chillies rellenos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray two individual 2 cup casseroles with nonstick cooking spray and set aside.

title: pumpkin blossom patties
directions: Chop blossoms and basil and add to slightly beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and fry in hot oil like pancakes.
Drop by large tablespoonfuls in oil.
Fry on both sides and put on platter. Sprinkle with grated Romano cheese.

title: "chicken again!"
directions: Spray vegetable oil in shallow 2 1/2 to 3-quart baking dish. Place chicken, potatoes and carrots in dish.
In bowl, mix together tomato sauce and herbs.
Pour over chicken and vegetables; mix well.
Lay pepper and onion rings evenly over top.
Cover and bake at 350° one hour.
Remove cover and continue to bake until vegetables are tender and chicken is done, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: berried delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill.
Beat cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half of the whipped topping.
Spread over crust. Arrange strawberries in even layer.
Using cold milk, prepare pudding as directed.
Pour over berries. Chill several hours or overnight.
Before serving, spread remaining whipped topping over pudding.
Garnish with additional strawberries.

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water together and set aside.
Cream together the brown sugar, sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Add the eggs and mix well. Add flour, soda and salt; mix well. Stir in the oatmeal mix.
Pour in a 10 x 15-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add soup and milk.
Melt cheese and add to mixture.
Cook broccoli and add to mixture.
Simmer together 10 minutes.

title: pot au feu soup(serves 10)
directions: Wash the meat in cold water and put in a pot. Add the water, bones and spices.
Bring to a quick boil. Skim until all of the fat has disappeared and the stock is clear.
Lower the heat and continue to simmer for 1 hour.

title: pan-fried potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4 inch thick slices.
In a 12-inch skillet melt the butter or margarine over medium heat.
Add sliced potatoes and cook, turning occasionally for 20 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: peach punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes about 3/4 gallon.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Dump in apple pie filling, crushed pineapple and cake mix.
Cut up 1 stick margarine over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Check for doneness.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together (using 1 cup of Bisquick at a time).
Shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Cook corn syrup and sugar in 3 qt. pan over medium heat until it boils.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter then mix in Rice Krispies. Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch bits and spread over Krispies.
Chill about 5 minutes until firm on top and cut into bars.

title: quick mix 2 egg cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Add shortening, 1/2 cup milk and blend together.
Beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes or by hand 300 strokes.
Add remaining milk, vanilla and eggs.
Blend together and beat an additional 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased pans (9-inch layer pans).
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be baked in Bundt pan.

title: tea cakes
directions: Sift flour,
soda, cream of tartar and salt; set aside. Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Add flour to creamed mixture, a little at a time, until all
flour	has
been added.
Grease cookie sheet.	Roll and cut out.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spicy catfish
directions: Marinate catfish in lemon juice and hot sauce for at least 1/2 day.
Brush fish with skim and Pet milk and dip in the 7 seasonings mixed.
In an electric skillet at 400°, put margarine in pan and fry fish for 3 minutes on each side.
Serve at once.

title: baked pecans
directions: Beat egg white stiff.
Mix all together.
Pour on buttered sheet pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix cranberries, apples and sugar.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix oatmeal and sugar.
Sprinkle on top of other mixture, then drizzle butter on mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Mix together and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: aunt rose's mincemeat
directions: Grind all of fruit and raisins together.
Cook ground beef and drain.
Add all other ingredients; cook until done.
Taste as you go along.
You might want it spicier.
The ground beef should be ground coarse.

title: haystacks
directions: Mix oats, coconut, chocolate and nuts in large bowl.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil margarine, milk and sugar.
Pour over oat mixture and mix until chocolate melts.
Drop at once by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let set.
(Place in refrigerator if making on a hot day.)

title: sylvia's mashed potato candy
directions: Cook up one good-sized potato and mash well.
Start beating in powdered sugar into the mashed potato.
It will take about 1 box powdered sugar.
Mix enough powdered sugar into the potato until it is stiff enough to roll, then roll it out as if you were making a jelly roll and spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll and slice off.
Delicious candy!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring Karo syrup, sugar and salt to a boil. Add raw peanuts, stirring constantly. When liquid turns caramel colored, add 1 teaspoon soda and stir well.
Pour onto lightly greased (Pam) heavy duty tinfoil.
Let set until cold.
Break into pieces by tapping with handle of butter knife.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, soy, pepper, beans, and 2/3 cup onion. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. Sprinkle remaining 2/3 cup of onions over beans, bake 5 minutes.

title: busy day stew
directions: Place all ingredients into rectangular baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Don't peek.
Serves 4.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Slowly blend white vinegar into mustard. Add water, sugar, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and whole cloves. Simmer 10 minutes. Cool. Pour over eggs. Add onion slices. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until crumbly.
Press half of mixture into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in diced rhubarb.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook over low heat until clear and thick.
Pour over rhubarb and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve warm or cold.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with sliced potatoes.
Top with chopped onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Lay raw pork chops atop onions.
Repeat layers of potatoes and onions and pour 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup atop.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and add seasoning.
Cool.
Layer lettuce, tomatoes, onion, kidney beans and cheese.
Then layer hamburger on top.
Add Fritos before dressing.
Pour 1/2 bottle of Italian dressing over the top just before serving.
Stir and serve immediately.

title: chocolate fudge brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients together and pour into a greased 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Thickly butter bread, cube and lay side by side in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover heavily with cheese.
Beat eggs. Add milk and salt and beat, then pour over cheese and bread. Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight (two nights are best).
Let warm to room temperature then bake 35 minutes at 375°. Can top with sausage, ham and bacon.

title: kielbasa and potatoes
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and set aside.
Add onion to drippings and saute until golden brown.
Add potato cubes and stir over low heat until lightly browned (about 5 minutes).
Cook kielbasa in boiling salted water for 15 minutes; drain and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Add kielbasa to potatoes.
Add red peppers and stir over low heat for another 10 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pile on a serving platter and sprinkle with reserved crisp bacon.
Serve with dark bread.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Cook chicken and sausage in oil in a Dutch oven until chicken is golden brown; remove chicken and sausage.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in Dutch oven.
Saute onions and next 3 ingredients in drippings.
Add water, rice, salt, peppers, chicken and sausage.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and water is absorbed.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pinch biscuits into small pieces into 2-quart baking dish. Beat eggs; add other ingredients and pour over biscuits.
Bake in 375° oven.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Fold in other ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Set in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Top with sour cream.
Add remaining 1/2 mixture.
Chill.

title: spicy fries
directions: Make an egg and flour batter.
Wash and cut potatoes lengthwise, leaving peelings on.
Mix pepper and salt into batter. Dip potato strips into batter and fry in oil until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and form into a ball.
Hollow out a place in the center for strawberry jam.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese and bacon muffins
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease and heat skillet, muffin pans or cornstick molds.
Beat egg in a mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes for skillet or 15 to 18 minutes for muffins and sticks.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add pineapple and grated carrots; mix well.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake springs back.
This makes two 9-inch layer pans.
If using tube pan, bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Frost with my Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, beat egg, slightly.
Add melted butter to which onion has been added.
(If fresh onion, cook in the butter a few minutes.)
Add corn, muffin mix and less than 1/3 cup of the reserved liquid from the whole kernel corn.
(I used about half the 1/3 cup.) Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven before it is completely set in the center.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat three egg whites until stiff.
Spread on top of pie and bake at 350° until brown.

title: pecan butterballs
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Form into 1-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Cool. Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: old fashioned jelly roll
directions: Combine baking powder, salt and eggs in bowl.
Beat, adding sugar gradually until mixture becomes thick and bright colored. gradually fold in flour, then vanilla.
Turn into 15 x 10-inch pan which has been lined with wax paper and greased and floured.
Bake at 400° for 13 minutes.
Turn cake out on cloth or towel, dusted with powdered sugar.
Quickly remove paper and cut off crisp edges of cake.
Roll cake, rolling cloth up in cake.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Unroll, spread cake with jelly and reroll.
Wrap in cloth; place on cake rack to finish cooling.

title: penne from heaven
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet saute mushrooms in oil for 5 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, basil and salt.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes, drain pasta and add to the skillet.
Stir in cheese heat thru.
5 servings.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain off water.
Add remainder of ingredients; mix well.
Season to your taste.

title: cranberry-apple pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, let stand 10 minutes.
Pour into 9 inch pie crust, Adjust top crust and flute edge.
Bake 400° 45 to 60 minutes, or until apples are tender.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and Crisco.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs for top. To remaining, add molasses, 3/4 cup hot water and beaten egg. Mix.
(Will be slightly lumpy.)
Add baking soda, dissolved in 1/4 cup hot water.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Sprinkle crumbs on top. Bake 5 minutes at 450°, then 30 minutes at 375°.

title: hearty beef and vegetable soup
directions: The day before serving, place beef, marrow bone, 1 tablespoon salt and 4 quarts water in a large kettle.
Cover and bring to boiling.
Skim surface.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
It is important that you use Duncan Hines cake mix, not another brand.
(That's what I was told.) Drop by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheesy onion buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Combine milk, 1/4 cup margarine, sugar and salt in a mixing bowl; stir until butter melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Add egg, yeast mixture and 2 cups flour; mix well.
Stir in cheese, onion and enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a well-floured surface; knead 8 to 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Shape into a ball.
Place dough in a well-greased bowl; brush top with melted margarine.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down; cover and let rest 10 minutes.

title: curried cauliflower
directions: Divide cauliflower into flowerets.
Cook approximately 15 minutes in boiling water; drain well.
Mix together soup, cheese and curry powder in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
To this add cauliflower.
Toss bread crumbs with butter.
Spread evenly on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: sour cream clam dip
directions: Combine all.
Chill to let flavors "marry".
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: famous cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Heat shortening barely enough to melt it and add to milk and yeast mixture.
Add salt, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat with rotary beater until well blended.
Add enough of remaining cup of flour by hand to make dough stiff enough to handle.
Pour onto well floured board and work in additional flour until stiff.

title: ice cream
directions: Heat milk and half of sugar.
Mix rest of sugar, flour and eggs; beat until light.
Add to boiling milk; cook until thickened.
Add vanilla and cream before freezing.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: punch-bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 2 cake layers according to directions on box.
Split in half with a thread and place one section in bottom of punch bowl.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cool and pour sugar mixture into a 5-quart freezer container.
Stir in next 4 ingredients and freeze until firm.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick butter; press into sprayed 9 x 13 pan. Mix confectioners sugar, 1 stick melted butter, softened cream cheese and 2 beaten eggs. Pour over crust and top with pecans. Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt oleo and mix with crushed pretzels.
Put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° in oven.
Let cool.

title: easy pepper steak
directions: Slice beef into very thin strips.
In skillet over medium-high heat, heat 1 Tbsp. oil.
Brown beef.
Remove beef and add 1 Tbsp. oil.
Add peppers and onion.
Cook over medium heat until tender-crisp.
Add gravy and sauce.
Return beef to pan. Heat.
Serve over rice.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mix egg yolks and next 6 ingredients while eggs are warm. Fill egg whites with mixture and top each with half a green and black olive.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Dust with paprika (optional) and garnish dish with parsley sprigs (optional).

title: ham and cheese delight
directions: Cook onions in 1 tablespoon butter until transparent.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish, bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.
You may refrigerate overnight before baking.

title: noodle dressing
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain, rinse and set aside.
Cook bacon and crumble.
In bacon grease cook all, except noodles.
When vegetables are tender, drain off bacon grease and combine with noodles.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Crumble chips in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown ground beef and onion. Add seasonings, tomato sauce and taco seasoning. Spoon over tortilla chips.
Mix cottage cheese and sour cream together.
Spoon over beef mixture.
Top with cheese. Cover with foil. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge (with velveeta cheese)
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Add to sugar and cocoa.
Mix well. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or larger or into a cookie sheet.
Keeps very well.

title: fair's rhubarb pie
directions: Put rhubarb in large bowl.
Mix sugar, flour and salt and pour over rhubarb.
Add beaten eggs; mix well and pour into a 9-inch crust.
Cover with vented top crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Best ever!

title: chess pie
directions: Beat brown sugar, eggs and melted butter.
Add flour and milk. Pour into crust.
Bake until top is brown at 350°, about 1 hour.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat
oven
to
In bowl, combine apples, milk and cinnamon;
set aside.
In another bowl, mix butter, 1 cup biscuit mix;
mix until crumbly.
Stir in apple mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish.
In another bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup biscuit mix and sugar; cut in 2 tablespoons of butter until crumbly; add nuts.	Sprinkle on apple mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: spinach and orange salad(individual servings)
directions: Pass the Honey Dijon Salad Dressing.

title: salmon cakes(lo-cal)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Shape mixture into 4 patties.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 5 minutes on each side.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and form in a ball.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Longer refrigeration is better.

title: hamburgers on the grill
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Mix well; shape into patties. Grill over hot coals until thoroughly cooked.
Makes 8 servings.

title: salami sticks
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator 3 days.
Mix each day.
On third day, roll into 4 rolls.
Bake at 175° to 200° for 8 hours. Bake on top of broiler pan.

title: black-eyed pea cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, soda, salt, eggs, buttermilk, oil, onion, jalapeno peppers, and corn; Mix well. Brown and drain sausage; add to cornmeal mixture. Add black-eyed peas and cheese. Mix and pour into greased baking pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bride's pink punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Dissolve Kool-Aid in 2-quarts cold water.
Add sugar and stir in gelatin mixture. Refrigerate.
Add beverage just before serving.
Add sherbet last before serving.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion in butter; add soup. Mix well. Add rice and 1 teaspoon salt. Place in covered casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix soup, oil, sugar and vinegar.
Cook for 15 minutes over low heat.
Pour over sliced pepper, sliced onion and cooked carrots.
Let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: butter biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients and fill mini muffin tins (almost full). Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 36.

title: international stinger
directions: Build in rock glass with cubed ice.

title: party treats
directions: Spread one package of rolls on cookie sheet.
Mix cheese, sugar an vanilla well and spread over rolls.
Cover with second package of rolls.
Beat egg well and brush on top, then sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake in a 350 degree oven until browned on top. Cool before cutting.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill before serving.
Serve with chips.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well. Add buttermilk, eggs and vegetable oil. Stir well.
Stir in cheese, corn, onion, bacon and pimento.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan or 8-inch black iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 8 or 9 servings.

title: hobo dinner
directions: For each serving, lay out 1 large square of foil.
On this, add in order, the following:
1 hamburger patty, onion slices, sliced potato and carrot. Add salt, pepper and 1 pat of margarine. Close foil and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until veggies are tender.

title: lo-cal strawberry pie
directions: Mix flour, powdered sugar and margarine; press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix boiling water, jello and cornstarch; cook until thick and allow to cool.
Fill cooled crust with 3 to 6 cups fresh berries.
Pour cooled sauce over berries.
Refrigerate until serving.
Serves 6.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Mix pie filling and lemon peel in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Combine baking mix and butter in small bowl.
Add water.
Stir vigorously until dough forms a ball and cleans bowl.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown.
Makes 9 servings.

title: berry pies made with jello base
directions: Cook water, sugar, cornstarch and salt until clear, stirring constantly.
While hot add jello and stir until dissolved.
When cool add fresh berries and pour into baked pie crust.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to butter mixture alternating with dry ingredients.
Mix well.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk, flour and cheese.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are soft, especially broccoli (add water if necessary).
Gradually add all milk to flour in shaker; add to vegetables gradually.
Stir and boil until thickened.
Then add cheese just before serving.
Turn off heat and stir.

title: microwave hot tuna sandwich loaf
directions: In mixing bowl, combine eggs, tuna, onion, salt, pepper, mustard and mayonnaise; mix well.
Cut off lengthwise top 1/2 of French bread.
With a fork, hollow out bottom 2/3 of loaf.
Save unused bread crumbs.
Fill loaf with tuna mixture.
Cut cheese slices in 1/2 and place over tuna mixture; replace top of bread. Cook, uncovered, on paper towel, 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Slice 1 to 2-inches thick for serving.

title: cake topping
directions: Mix and boil 10 minutes, then add coconut and nuts.
Pour over cake.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut candied cherries in half.
Mix coconut and baking cocoa in large bowl.
Stir in condensed milk and vanilla.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Press 1 cherry half into each cookie.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until almost set.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Store loosely at room temperature.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and roll into ball, door knob size. Mix tomato sauce and sugar together and pour over meatballs. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover, turn meatballs over and bake 15 minutes more.
Makes large amount.

title: skorthalia garlic sauce
directions: Mix first
ingredients in a large bowl; set aside to cool. Chop
garlic
cloves
in
Cuisinart.
Add potatoes; mix well. Then
starting
with vinegar, add oil.
Alternate until used; end with
vinegar.
Add pepper; mix until smooth.
Last, add cold water and mix until creamy.

title: spaghetti-pizza style
directions: Cook and drain the spaghetti.
Beat milk and eggs; toss with spaghetti.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Add remaining pizza items.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve 8 to 10.

title: chocolate buttermallow cake
directions: Bake cake mix in oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches as directed on package.
Spread Butterscotch Filling over top of cooled cake to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over filling. Frost sides and top of cake with Marshmallow Frosting.
Melt chocolate; dip back of spoon into chocolate and form swirls on frosting.

title: shrimp marinara
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in oil until tender. Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar and seasonings. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until thick and bubbly, stirring frequently. Add shrimp. Cover and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Serve over spaghetti. Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together thoroughly all ingredients except pecans, then stir in pecans (halves or chopped).
Pour into unbaked crust and bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and stir only to blend.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into deep fat
or
oil heated
to 350° and fry 2 to 3 minutes, or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Makes 18.

title: janet's spaghetti-noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add garlic.
Stir in soup and water. Add 1/2 the cheese.
Cook noodles and spaghetti per directions on package.
Drain.
Add cooked noodles and spaghetti.
Mix well.
Put in casserole.
Add remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sole with asparagus
directions: Soak the sole in lemon juice for 20 minutes and drain.
Spread the mustard on the bottom of the fish.
Generously shake on the Parmesan cheese.
Take 2 to 3 pieces of asparagus and place in the center of the fillet.
Roll the fish.
Place in greased baking dish.
Pour white wine over fish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until fish is done.
Sprinkle with dill and paprika for color.

title: laguna beach pecan chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Melt butter over low heat. Grind pecans. Flatten chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness. Dip chicken into mustard mixture and roll in ground pecans. Arrange chicken in single layer in lightly greased baking pan. Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown/tender.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Combine all and cook at 300 degrees for 3 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: teriyaki miniatures
directions: Combine soy sauce, water, sugar, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix meat and crumbs and stir in soy mixture.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add to any kind of meat.

title: no time soup
directions: In crock-pot mix tomato paste with 1 can of water; add remaining ingredients (Cavender's to taste; I sprinkle heavily over top), then stir to mix evenly.
Cook all day on low or half day on high.
Serves 6.

title: bread stuffing(3 quarts for 12 pound turkey)
directions: I use 1 teaspoon of all 4 seasonings.

title: fresh corn and green chili casserole
directions: Blend partially frozen corn with a little milk in processor to a thick mash consistency.
Then mix all ingredients in large bowl and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Can bake, freeze and reheat.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar. Combine butter, cocoa and water in a saucepan. Bring to a rapid boil. Stir well, stir in slightly beaten eggs. Pour into a greased pan 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes. When done and while cake is still hot, spread with icing.

title: chili cheese topping or munch
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in chili powder and garlic salt; drizzle over popcorn in a large bowl.
Toss gently to coat well.
Pour into lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Spread evenly and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 5 minutes at 325° or until cheese melts.
Remove from oven and stir.
Serve as a topping for soups, chili, etc.
or as a snack.
Makes 2-quarts.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all the ingredients together and mix well.
A blender may be used!

title: potato pancakes
directions: Note:
Omit salt
and baking powder, if using self-rising flour.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and pour into pie crust. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta 10 minutes.
Pour cool water over pasta to stop the cooking.
In large bowl, mix pasta, sour cream, Ranch dressing, vegetable mix and pepperoni.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in bottom of large baking dish.
Put chicken on top.
Pour soup over all.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serves 4.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Cream together shortening and sugars. Add vanilla. Add eggs and beat. Add flour mixture. Add oats and chocolate chips. Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight in a large kettle; drain in the morning.
Add water to make 5 quarts; add bone and simmer for 2 hours or until beans fall apart.
Add potatoes, onions, celery and garlic.
Simmer one more hour.
Remove the bone, cut up the meat and put the meat back in.
Season to taste.

title: cinnamon swirl cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: orange bowknots
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm. Soften yeast in this mixture.
Add eggs, orange juice and peel; beat thoroughly.
Add flour; mix until a soft dough.
Cover; let stand 10 minutes.
Knead on lightly floured surface.
Place in greased bowl; let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 2 hours.
Punch down.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in a 10-inch strip, 1/2-inch
wide.
Tie each in a knot.
Arrange on a greased baking sheet.
Cover.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake in hot 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Spread with orange topping.
(Can omit orange peel.)

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Mix and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, margarine or butter and cocoa to boil and boil hard nonstop boil for 1 minute, then remove from heat and quickly add 3 cups quick cooking oats, 1/2 cup peanut butter, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract and 1/2 to 1 cup nuts, if desired.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let stand 1/2 hour until dry.

title: poor man's hot dish
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion until brown.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add soup; stir until blended.
Add cabbage chunks; toss lightly.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: curly noodle dinner
directions: Break ground meat into large pieces while adding it to a large skillet.
Cook meat over high heat until beef is brown or turkey sausage is no longer pink.
Drain off fat.
Stir in the seasoning packet from the Oriental noodles, undrained tomatoes and undrained corn.
Slightly break up the noodles while adding them to the meat mixture in the skillet.
Stir until combined.
Bring mixture to boiling, then reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for about 10 minutes, or until noodles are tender and flavors are blended.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Arrange in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Mix rice, soups, onions, milk and cheese.
Spread over broccoli and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in soups and water.
Pour just enough of soup mixture in the bottom of a baking dish to cover the bottom of the dish.
Place uncooked rice on top of this.
Then pour 1/2 of the liquid mixture over rice.
Place chicken pieces over this and pour the rest of the soup mixture over it.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Recipe doubles easily.
Makes a great Sunday dinner.

title: cocktail cookies
directions: Make dough into a ball.
Chill (overnight if possible).
Roll thin and cook on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until edges are slightly browned.
Let cool on sheet before moving.

title: popovers
directions: Grease muffin tins well.
Beat egg until fluffy.
Add flour slowly.
Add milk and beat again.
Use baster to fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Place in cold oven.
Turn heat to 450°.
Makes 4 to 5 regular size or 1 dozen cocktail size.
Regular muffins bake in 35 minutes; cocktail muffins bake in 20 to 25 minutes.
May be filled with grated cheese or ham.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix orange juice, sherbet, apple juice and pineapple juice. Add ginger ale just before serving.
Yields about 10 servings.

title: sausage stuffed shells
directions: If using link sausage, prick with fork and parboil in a small amount of water in covered skillet for 5 minutes.
Drain and chop sausage.
Fry with onion until brown, stirring often.
Spoon off excess fat.
Mix bread crumbs, egg and parsley with sausage.
Cook shells according to directions and drain well.
Spoon sausage into each shell.
Pour half of sauce on bottom of casserole.
Arrange shells in dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly hot.
Remove foil; sprinkle cheese over top and bake 10 more minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Make the cake mix.
(Substitute 1/2 cup powdered chocolate with Royal instant chocolate pie filling.)
Pour half the cake mix in greased and floured pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, eggs and flour together; put in buttered casserole dish.
Melt butter in skillet; pinch off bread and stir into butter.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit surprise cornmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray nonstick spray into muffin tin cups or use paper cups.
In medium bowl, thoroughly combine the two kinds of flour, cornmeal and baking powder.

In a small mixing bowl, lightly beat egg whites. Stir in the oil, grape juice concentrate, crushed pineapple, pineapple juice and skim milk. Add the egg and fruit mixture to the dry ingredients, mixing just to moisten.
Fill 12 muffin cups 2/3 full and drop about 1/2 teaspoon of fruit jam on top of each muffin.

Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in the center of the muffin comes out clean. One serving (1 muffin) contains 1 starch/bread exchange, 1/2 fruit exchange, 1 fat exchange, 152 calories, 25 grams carbohydrates, 3 grams protein, 5 grams fat, a trace of fiber, 0 milligrams cholesterol, 100 milligrams sodium and 28% calories from fat.
Makes 12 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend all ingredients and pour into 2 floured and greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix juices in large container.
Add cherries, pineapple, frozen lemonade, frozen orange juice and large package of lemonade (follow directions on package).
Add sugar to taste.
Slice lemons and oranges in small pieces and add to punch.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Serves 45 to 50.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Run cookies through blender.
Cream together cream cheese and set aside. Mix pudding and milk together.
Add vanilla and Cool Whip.
Add cream cheese.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Dump all ingredients into microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove and stir; microwave 1 more minute. Remove; add 1 tablespoon vanilla and 1/2 cup chopped nuts, if desired.
Mix and pour into a buttered dish.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add sour cream.
Sift flour and soda; add gradually to creamed mixture.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix and heat slowly until cheese is melted.
Serve warm or cold with taco chips.

title: potato soup
directions: In large pot, melt butter.
Add onion, chopped fine.
Cook until tender over low heat.
Add 1 gallon water; bring to boil. Add celery and carrots, chopped very fine.
Cut potatoes very fine and add them.
Add chives, salt and pepper.
Add balance of water and milk.
Reduce to low heat.
Cook for 2 to 3 hours or more, until cooked down and thick.

title: west hanen cake
directions: Cut package of dates in half.
Pour hot water and soda over them.
Cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add to date mixture. Add salt, eggs, vanilla, cocoa and flour.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken rice divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain. Arrange in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of the cheese.
Add chicken.
Season to taste.
Top with rice.

title: easy brunch casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with butter.
Put cubed or torn bread in dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, onion powder and pepper.
Pour mixture over cheese and bread.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon, mushrooms and/or broccoli over top of bread and cheese in dish.
Cover and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake uncovered until set, about one hour.
(Tent with foil if top browns too quickly.) Serves 12.

title: chocolate-caramel tortillas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly coat cookie sheet(s) with nonstick cooking spray.
Stack tortillas and cut in 8 wedges (you'll have 48).
Arrange wedges in a single layer on prepared cookie sheet(s).
Lightly spray tops with cooking spray.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes until golden and crisp.
Slice onto wire rack to cool. Meanwhile, melt chocolate in a small saucepan over low heat.
Put caramels and water in another small saucepan and stir constantly over
low heat until caramels melt.
Working with about 12 at a time, place wedges on a wire rack and drizzle with chocolate and caramel.
Remove to waxed paper to harden.
If necessary, remelt caramel and/or chocolate over low heat between batches.
Store airtight with waxed paper between layers.

title: perfect baked turkey
directions: The day before or a few hours before cooking, make a soft paste of dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, olive oil, salt, pepper and a little vinegar in proportions to make spreadable.
Rub the bird well inside and out with this, then place inside a whole onion, cut in half, 2 pieces celery and little parsley.
Lay 2 pieces of bacon across breast and stick hunks of butter (about 1 stick) between drumstick and body.
Soak cheesecloth or dish towel in olive oil. Lay over bird and put in uncovered roaster.
Add 1 or 2 cups stock. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes per pound for a 7 to 10 pound turkey or 18 minutes per pound for a 15 to 18 pound turkey.
Baste once or twice.
Browns beautifully and juicy.

title: tropical fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Start in a cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, place pie filling and pineapple and sprinkle cake mix on top.
Melt butter and spread over cake. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
May add nuts, if desired.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage and drain.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fish fry
directions: For 4 servings, you will need
1 3/4 to 2 pounds baby beef ribs.

title: jiffy fruit cobbler
directions: Note:
When using canned or frozen fruit, omit the water and sweeten to taste.

title: diced apple cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour in tube pan, coated with oil and flour.

title: my mom's favorite chocolate trifle
directions: Use a
clear
bowl.
Put
of cubed cake in bottom. Drizzle with
of Kahlua, then 1/2 of pudding, 1 container of Cool
Whip
then
of crushed bars.
Repeat in the same order. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: tupperware pie crust
directions: Place all ingredients in a large Tupperware bowl.
Cover and be sure to seal.
Shake until all ingredients are mixed well. Mixture will stop thumping.
Roll out; will make 1 double crust.

title: rice and beans
directions: Place 1/2 cup oil in electric skillet.
Add chopped onion, green pepper, tomato and spices to taste.
Saute in oil until tender or lightly browned.
Add tomato sauce, then add rice and beans with 2 cans of water and simmer.
More water may need to be added.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pork schnitzel
directions: Pound pork 1/4 to 1/8 inch thick.
Cut small slits around edges to prevent curling.
Coat meat with mixture of the flour, seasoning salt and pepper.
Combine egg and milk.

title: sage squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender enough to mash.
Drain well and mash.
Mix in 1 teaspoon of the grated cheese.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a baking dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Press crescent rolls in pie pan.
Put hamburger on top of pressed rolls.
Next, add shredded cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Top with shredded lettuce, onions, cheese and taco sauce.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add Coca-Cola, pineapple and sugar.
Mix well and place in refrigerator.
When mixture is chilled and beginning to set, add Cool Whip and cheese and allow to congeal.

title: mom's very own roast beef or chicken
directions: In a big pot brown the roast beef in the butter very well on all sides with the lid closed.
Remove aside on a plate and in the same butter, brown the garlic and carrots until golden brown; remove from pan to another plate.
Replace the roast beef or chicken in the pot; place on top the tomato, coarsely cut, salt, pepper and enough water to cover the meat.
Cover and cook for an hour or until tender.
When almost done, place a few peeled potatoes (depending on the servings), the carrots and the garlic in the pot.
Cook until all is done.
If liquid is too much, cook, uncovered.
Serve meat on a platter with vegetables around.
You could substitute mashed potatoes for fresh ones.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add chopped onion, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add Ranch Style beans, tomato paste or puree and water.
Boil until thick and juicy.

title: chicken salad casserole(this is a big casserole.  half would be plenty for a small
directions: Mix all except last three ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Mix the last three ingredients and put on top of the chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Layer spinach, washed, dried and torn.
Then layer bacon, fried crisp and crumbled, then salt, pepper and sugar, sprinkled. Layer eggs, chopped, then lettuce, washed, dried and torn.
Layer peas, thawed at room temperature, then salt, pepper and sugar, sprinkled.
Mix together sour cream and mayo.
Spread mixture on top of salad about 1 hour before serving.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese and bacon bits on top.
Best if eaten the first couple of days.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: chicken-macaroni en casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 60 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
tags: cream of chicken soup plus milk

title: liver paste
directions: Blend liverwurst and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
May be used as a spread on crackers for appetizers.

title: white chili
directions: In crock pot or large pan, combine all ingredients, stirring in chicken broth last. Cook on low 8 to 10 hours (in crockpot). Serve with Monterey jack cheese and broken tortilla chips.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Heavily butter casserole dish.
Line with bread cubes.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour over cubes.
Cover tightly and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seafood mold
directions: Cook shrimp or crabmeat or crawfish.
Heat on low fire the tomato soup and cream cheese.
Add gelatin to hot soup.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a well oiled mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: apple cake(this is a good cake for company.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into a lightly greased Bundt pan and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add strawberries and juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Put 1/2 mixture in rectangular glass dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
When congealed, spread sour cream over top.
Then spoon the rest of the mixture over all.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: easter bread
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
