In large mixing bowl, beat the eggs and yolks until lemon colored. Gradually add sugar, butter, salt, vanilla, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Heat well; blend in milk and yeast mixture.
Add 6 cups flour; beat well.
By hand, stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn on floured surface; knead until smooth, sprinkle with raisins.
Knead 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Knead again.
Makes 3 loaves.
Put in loaf pans.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: pumpkin gingersnap pie
directions: Beat half and half and pie filling.
Mix in mixing bowl with wire whisk for 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in topping and remaining ingredients; spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm. Let stand at room temperature to soften before serving.

title: freezer marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar and shake well.
Can be frozen for later use.
Serve on London broil, chuck steak or venison.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients into a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until cheese melts, stirring often.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let cheese and sausage lay out a while.
Grate cheese.
Mix cheese, sausage and Bisquick together.
Work up like dough.
Pinch off and roll into little balls.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 15 or 20 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and take out 1/2 cup for topping.
To the remaining mix, add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: elegant rice salad
directions: Prepare the rice according to the package directions (I use Rice-A-Roni).
Let it cool to room temperature.
Drain the liquid from the artichokes into a large bowl; coarsely chop the artichoke hearts and add them to the bowl.
Add the olives, scallions, mayonnaise, pepper and the pimentos to the bowl.
Add the cooled rice, mixing well.
Refrigerate the salad at least 4 to 5 hours before serving.
Serves 12.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add to liquid mixture.
Pour in small, greased bread pans. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: slop cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into pan or pans.
Bake at 375° until center springs back when touched.
Just throw all ingredients in large mixing bowl and turn on mixer.
Batter is very thin so don't be alarmed.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Add vanilla after about the first pound.
Add and mix in sugar until you can form a ball that will stay on a toothpick for dipping.
In a double boiler, melt the wax and chocolate chips.
(Other coatings can be used.)
After the coating is melted, reduce heat to low. Form balls and place on waxed paper lined cookie sheets.
Dip and chill while you form more balls.
They freeze well.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: orange delight
directions: Measure the sherbet and set aside to soften, open pineapple, orange sections and measure all ingredients ready for quick put together.
Mix Knox gelatin and orange jello in large bowl.
Add boiling water and dissolve.
Add orange sherbet and mix well, making sure the sherbet is melted.
Add pineapple, orange sections, nuts, Cool Whip and marshmallows.
This will set up rather quickly. Makes a large container of dessert.
Keeps well for several days.

title: date pudding
directions: Dissolve brown sugar and hot water in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Mix and put in pan with water, sugar mix. Bake at 350°.

title: skillet chicken and cheese broccoli
directions: Heat butter in skillet. Add chicken and cook until browned. Add soup, water, pepper and broccoli. Heat to a boil; cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until done, then add cheese.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions using reserved pineapple juice mixed with the water. Dot bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter (spray with a vegetable spray coating first). Arrange pineapple slices on bottom of pan.
Place cherries in the center of the pineapple.
Pour batter over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients gently.
Best if left in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: mango pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in a little water. Add to Mango pulp.

Over medium heat constantly stirring, bring mango pulp to slow boil. As soon as it starts boiling, remove from heat. Cool to room temperature. Now blend in the heavy cream. Mix well. Pour into crust. Refrigerate until set.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix beans, peas, white corn, pimento, green pepper, chopped onion and celery.
Combine sugar, oil, vinegar and salt in a saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Pour over vegetables; cover and refrigerate.
Will keep a week.

title: mock fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick and foamy.
Add zucchini, coconut, nuts, fruit cake mix and raisins.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Divide batter equally between 2 greased and floured pans or use a round tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In bowl, combine sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar and onion juice.
Gradually beat in oil until mixture is thick and smooth. Stir in poppy seeds.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator. Good with fruit or regular salad.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: strawberry jello delight
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen sliced berries, crushed pineapple and bananas.
Mix well.
Turn 1/2 of mixture into 8-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.
Then spread sour cream and cover with the remaining gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: box-car barbecue
directions: Place roast in pan. Mix all ingredients and pour over roast. Bake at 300° for 5 to 6 hours. Remove bones and chop.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in bowl:
bean dip, sour cream, mayonnaise, taco mix (mixed together), avocados, tomatoes, onions, olives (on top with salt) and grated cheese all over.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each addition.
Combine baking powder, salt and flour.
Fold into batter.
Add vanilla.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick using as little flour as possible.
Cut into shapes.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: paul's pecans
directions: Whip egg and water.
Stir in nuts.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Sprinkle over nuts.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil until all butter is melted. All at once add flour and salt; beat until mixture forms a ball that leaves the sides of saucepan.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Spread mixture into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.

title: mushroom puffs(yield: 4 dozen)
directions: In a medium skillet, melt butter and saute mushrooms and onion over medium heat until golden brown, stirring occasionally. Drain.
Heat broiler.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese, egg yolks, parsley and seasonings until combined.
Spread evenly on cocktail bread slices and sprinkle with paprika.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes or until lightly browned and puffed.
Serve immediately.

title: beer dip
directions: Blend cheeses and beer until smooth. Hollow out the loaf of bread. Pour mixture into the center. Take chunks of bread and dip away.

title: beef burgundy with rice verte
directions: Place meat in bowl.
Sprinkle with bottled browning sauce. Toss lightly.
Brown in oil.
Add tomatoes, wine, bouillon cube and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add onions and carrots.
Cover and cook 45 minutes longer or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Blend cornstarch and water. Stir into stew mixture.
Cook stirring frequently until thickened.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over Rice Verte.
Yields 4 servings.

title: vienna bread - stuffed
directions: Score bread by slicing lengthwise to within 1/2-inch from the bottom in one-inch sections.
Turn and do the same in other direction.
Stuff bread with cheese and mushrooms.
Sprinkle onions, poppy seed and seasoned salt over top.

title: scripture cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the sugar and butter until very light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk to batter.
Stir in honey.
Fold in raisins, figs and almonds.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 1/3-inch loaf pans (two).
Bake 60 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper, sugar, onions and garlic as for meat loaf.
Parboil cabbage until soft enough to handle. Loosen leaves.
Cut out heavy grain.
Roll meat in cabbage leaf. Cut leftover cabbage and line pan.
Place rolls in pan with extra leaves between layers.
Pour tomato juice over all (can dilute with water). Cover, boil and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Let sit awhile before serving. Serve with sliced lemons.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and melted margarine.
Mix until creamy. Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix again until smooth. Mixture will be very thin.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: individual meat loaves
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Beat the egg and add bread.
Mix well.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pack into an individual casserole dish and bake in a moderate oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: slow cooker tex mex beef stew
directions: Break up tomatoes and drain, reserve liquid.
Place carrots and onions in slow cooker; arrange beef cubes on top of vegetables.
Combine chili seasoning mix and flour with tomato liquid.
Pour over meat.
Cover tightly and cook on high for 3 1/2 hours.
Add tomatoes, kidney beans and green pepper and continue cooking, covered, for 30 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: holiday basic batch recipe
directions: Mix dry ingredients in an 8-quart bowl.
Blend in shortening with a pastry cutter until mixture is crumbly.
May be stored in an airtight container in a cool, dry place for up to 6 months. Refrigeration is not necessary.
Yields 18 cups.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup cold water in top of double boiler.
Blend in sugar and salt.
Add remainder of water and when well blended stir constantly over low heat until mixture boils. Cover and cook over boiling water 10 minutes.
Gradually pour hot mixture over beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Return to double boiler and cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; add butter, lemon juice and rind and mix well.
Cool and pour into pie shell.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat, seasoning and sauce.
Bring to boil and let simmer 15 minutes.
Add chips and water.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: green beans and pork
directions: Brown
chopped	pork on high heat.
Add a little water; simmer until
pork
is soft, 15 minutes.	Add cut and cleaned beans. Cube
size	cooked	potatoes,
squash, zucchini and/or onions
may be
added.
When
beans
are 1/4 done, add shoyu, sugar and garlic powder.
Serve over rice.

title: pear crisp
directions: In 1 1/2-quart ovenproof bowl, toss pears with rum and dried fruit.
Set aside.
In separate bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over pears, tossing gently to mix.
Bake until crumbs are browned and pears are tender, about 30 minutes.
Spoon into serving bowl, top with flavored or plain whipped cream, if desired.

title: jalapeno squash
directions: Boil squash; drain.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Brown onion rings in bacon drippings.
Layer 1/2 of squash, bacon, onions and cheese in 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325 ° for 40 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: party punch
directions: Make syrup by bringing sugar and water to a boil.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill before serving.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: waldorf astoria stew
directions: Layer and do not stir. Cover and bake 5 hours at 250°. Biscuits are good with this.

title: rice and hot dogs
directions: Cook Minute rice; set aside.
Saute onion in oil; mix with catsup, water, vinegar, mustard, black pepper and cut up hot dogs. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, then serve on the rice.

title: quaker chocoat-chip cookies(yields 5 dozen cookies)
directions: Heat oven at 375°.
Mix all dry ingredients together, then add all others.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy, 12 to 13 minutes for crisp.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet and remove to wire rack.

title: stuffing(serve with turkey, beef or pork)
directions: Crumble and brown sausage over low heat.
Drain well.
Saute onion and celery in butter until yellow (stirring often to keep onion from browning).
Use low heat.
Combine all ingredients and add chicken broth.
Bake in large pan at 350° about 1 hour.
You can pour more chicken broth over it if you think it is too dry.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Spray Pam or margarine on 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Pour chopped apple pie mix filling in baking dish.
Mix melted butter, cake mix and nuts and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 35 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: coconut cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut.
Chill slightly. Shape into bite size balls; roll in coconut.
Serve with crackers.

title: finnish coffee bread
directions: Beat the sugar with the egg.
Add the milk, yeast, butter, salt and 2 cups of the flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add rest of the flour and let rise until double in size.
Knead down, cut into strips and braid into 3 or 4 loaves.
Let it rise again until light.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown.
When cool, decorate with frosting or fruit.
This is also good just as it is.

title: cold vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare cornbread per instructions and layer with other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: rum cake
directions: Beat according to cake mix directions and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and pierce well.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Blend sour cream and cream cheese; spread mixture on the center of plate.
Put layers of lettuce, tomato, onions and peppers.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover with taco sauce.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Slice carrots, onion and sweet peppers.
Chop lettuce fine. Add olive oil, mix in well, then vinegar or serve with mayonnaise.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut up.
Mix soups, rotel and chicken. Crunch doritos and put in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour mixture over doritos and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into 6 patties.
Fry on barbecue grill or in skillet on stove until browned on both sides. Place in 6 hamburger buns.
Insert on top of patty 1 slice of cheese.
(Heat from meat will melt the cheese.)

title: squash dressing
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Slice the squash and cook in microwave on paper towels (high power about 3 to 4 minutes).
Dry the squash on paper towels to get as much water out as possible. Mash squash and put into a bowl.
Melt butter and add diced onion. Add this to the squash.
Mix in soup, milk, egg and sour cream. Add the bag of stuffing.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° until brown, 20 to 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: english pea casserole
directions: Cook peas in margarine for 10 minutes.
In a medium bowl, mix all ingredients together and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Crush about 1/2 package of saltine crackers and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no peek beef
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a casserole dish or Dutch oven.
Cover and bake 3 hours at 300°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: oyster dressing(serves 40 moosers)
directions: Day Before:
Lay bread out on large pans to dry overnight. Do not toast.
In large pot, put 5 quarts of water, all butter, turkey parts and onion and boil for stock.
Debone turkey parts and chop with giblets.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Reserve 2/3 cup of this for topping.
To remainder, add baking powder, soda, cinnamon, beaten egg and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in 12 x 8-inch greased pan and sprinkle topping.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: peach ice cream pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients until dissolved.
Add peaches.
Mix together and chill.
After chilled, put in baked crust that is cooled.
Chill until time of serving.

title: sweet and sour shrimp
directions: In a large skillet, put everything except rice and shrimp. Stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add shrimp; cook until pink.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: lemon cheese bundt cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine margarine, butter and cream cheese.
Add 2 eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add flour slowly until all ingredients are blended.
Add extracts.
Pour batter into a prepared Bundt pan (spray with Pam).
Bake at 325° for one hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes clean.

title: cabbage pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix water and flour.
Combine with beef.
Add sour cream, onion and celery.
Crumble bacon into beef mixture.
Place one pie crust in pan and cover bottom of crust with shredded cabbage.
Top cabbage with meat mixture. Place second crust on top.
Bake until crust is brown.

title: microwave baked apples
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients.
Spread over the apples.
Bake in microwave for 6 to 8 minutes on High.
(I double the sauce for a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.)

title: miracle pie recipe
directions: Put ingredients in blender and blend well (or use an egg beater and beat well).
Pour into well buttered 10-inch pie pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Crust will form on bottom and rest on top.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out 1/4 of dough.
Slice into quarters.
Place a peeled and cored apple on each quarter.
Fill the cored center of the apple with cinnamon-sugar.
Top with 1/2 teaspoon butter or margarine.
Enclose the apple with the dough and stretch the dough around it to seal it.
Place in cake pan.
Bake the dumplings at 375° for 40 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir in eggs and oil.
Fold in chocolate chips, cherry pie filling and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until tests done, approximately 35 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar.

title: pepper and corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine corn, cream cheese and peppers in covered casserole dish.
Bake uncovered for about 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, stir butter, shortening, and sugar until creamy.
In a separate bowl, sift together cake flour and baking powder.
Add one egg, portion of flour and milk alternately until all eggs are used, beating thoroughly with mixer (slow speed). Add vanilla and lemon last.
Pour into a greased bundt pan, and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hour.

title: cobbler crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and margarine; add egg and vanilla.
Mix rest of ingredients and add to margarine mixture. Drop dough by spoonfuls onto hot fruit.
Bake 20 minutes and then fork dough to spread evenly.
Bake an additional 15 minutes or more until brown.

title: venison "sloppy joes"
directions: Place venison roast in crock-pot.
Season with seasoned salt. Cook on high for 4 hours.
Switch to low and cook overnight. Remove roast.
Dispose of liquid.
Cool meat.
When cool, chop meat fine and add enough sauce to moisten meat.
Heat meat again and serve on buns.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.	Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: moist chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy. Mix in flour and baking soda; stir in chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from cookie sheets. Cool on wire racks. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: sandra's pot pie(club member: amanda speed)
directions: Boil chicken and debone. Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Add broth and soup. Mix margarine, flour and milk; pour over chicken. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken salad superb
directions: Day Before:
Simmer chicken in water to half cover.
Remove meat from bones (4-5).
Store in refrigerator in broth. When ready to serve, remove chicken from broth.
Add celery, green pepper and onion.
Mix the remaining ingredients and toss with chicken mixture.

title: mushroom strudel
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add the next 4 ingredients; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in bread crumbs.
Cool to room temperature.
Heat oven to 375°.
Layer 3 fillo leaves on damp kitchen towel, brushing each with melted butter.
Spoon 1/2 mushroom mixture on short end of leaves in 2 to 3-inch wide strip, turning long side of fillo leaves in about 1 inch to keep filling in place.
Lift towel, using it to roll, starting from narrow end with filling.
Place roll, seam side down, in lightly buttered pan.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Brush top and sides of dough with melted butter.

title: no stir-fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix this cake like any fruitcake.
Line the pan with foil and bake for 1 hour or until done.
If you follow this recipe exactly, it will turn out wonderful.
The Bible is the same way.
Bake in a 325° oven.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Simmer onion in butter until soft.
Add beef and garlic and sprinkle with the flour and seasonings.
Add mushrooms and cook about 5 minutes, stirring now and then to brown beef a bit.
Add soup and simmer 10 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Heat gently and don't allow to boil.
Serve over Chinese noodles and garnish with chopped parsley.

title: john's steak chili(chili cook off entry - 1994)
directions: Have your steaks cubed and cut up into small chunks.
Brown in a 4-quart Dutch oven; add spices and simmer 20 minutes.
Put celery and onion in food processor and shred.
Put in onion, celery, tomato paste and tomatoes.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add chili hot beans and simmer at least 30 minutes.
Stir often.
May add more chili powder to taste.

title: beef and bacon super chili
directions: In a large chili pot, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from pot and drain grease away.
Brown ground chuck until no pink remains. Add onion and green pepper.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: delicious macaroni salad
directions: Mix all together.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked turkey, chicken or hen
directions: Wash and clean bird.
Rub outside and inside with salt and sage.
On the inside of the bird, place 1 or 2 stalks of celery and 1 stick of margarine.
Put in a brown oven bag or cover with Reynolds Wrap.
Place in pan on the breast of the bird and bake at 325° until done.
Twenty minutes before taking out of oven, turn bird on its back and brown the breast.
Let cool 30 minutes before trying to slice.

title: sybil's poppy seed chicken
directions: Season and boil chicken; debone and cut in bite-size pieces. Place in buttered casserole dish (9 x 13-inches).
Mix soup and sour cream into a saucepan.
Heat and pour over chicken.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients and cook over medium heat until hot.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour covered. Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour to 45 minutes or until sauce is thick and chicken is done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a medium mixing bowl combine flour and baking soda; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl combine margarine, granulated sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and dry pudding mix.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: oatmeal cake(this is the cake my mom would make, i love it.)
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cover and let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugars, beating until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Bake for about 50 to 55 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Add applesauce and water.
Mix well.
Add shortening, eggs, allspice, cloves and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: cheeseburger macaroni
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner according to directions on box.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain excess fat.
Combine thoroughly remaining ingredients with beef mixture and macaroni dinner.
Season to taste and place in 2-quart buttered casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: orange baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and liquids. Brush chicken generously.
Place chicken, skin side up, in a baking pan, basting occasionally with any remaining mixture.
Bake 1 hour or until chicken is done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool spaghetti.
Add remaining ingredients. Optional items to add are broccoli, cauliflower, sharp cheese (chopped).
Serve chilled.

title: window cleaner
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Spray on. Wipe off with old newspapers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 70 minutes.

title: coleslaw with sour cream dressing
directions: In medium bowl combine cabbage, carrots, bell pepper, celery and onion.
In small bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and toss until well coated.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.

title: orange-glazed sweet potatoes(serves 4)
directions: In a large skillet dissolve gelatin, brown sugar and salt in boiling water.
Add butter and bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add sweet potatoes.
Sprinkle with allspice and simmer, basting frequently, until syrup thickens and potatoes are glazed, about 15 minutes.

title: pear cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients with liquid and mix well.
Add pears and pecans.
Will be hard to stir.
Bake 50 minutes in greased and floured tube pan at 350°.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Boil 1 whole chicken until tender and can be pulled off the bone easily.
Boil carrots and potatoes until tender.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter.
Mix corn meal and flour together with 1/4 cup water.
Set all ingredients aside.

title: hush puppies(makes 5 dozen)
directions: In a medium bowl measure cornmeal, salt, garlic salt and onion.
In a large measuring cup measure buttermilk and add soda. Stir and let set for a couple of minutes.
Then stir into cornmeal.
Heat oil to 375°.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil. Fry only a few at a time, turning once.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix onion, eggs, mayonnaise and soup.
Layer broccoli, sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with stuffing and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Place meat in plastic bag; set in a deep bowl.
For marinade, combine cooking oil, soy, lemon juice, honey gark and ginger.
Pour over meat; close bag.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator; turn bag occasionally to distribute marinade.

title: judy's chicken potato casserole
directions: Mix together soup, milk and pepper. In a large casserole dish layer slices of potato, onion and chicken. Repeat layers. Pour soup mixture over layers and dot with butter. Bake covered at 375° for 1 hour and uncovered for 15 minutes. Serves 6-8.

title: italian broccoli
directions: Place butter or margarine in the frying pan; add broccoli, cooking until broccoli becomes a delicate brown.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: washington's delight
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix everything together.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Let cream cheese soften. Cream with sugar. Add sour cream then Cool Whip. Add fruit cocktail. Chill.

title: burn-your-mouth burritos
directions: Brown beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until cooked; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until heated through. Divide equally on individual warmed tortillas.
Top with cheese and roll up.

title: w v a sweetened corn pone
directions: Mix cornmeal, sugar, salt and boiling water early in the morning for evening meal.
Stir often.

title: easy popcorn balls
directions: Melt margarine, marshmallows and salt in saucepan over low heat.
Mix in popcorn.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef with onions and bell pepper included, then drain.
After draining, add cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups.
Bring to a boil so that it is nice and creamy.
Spread Doritos on bottom of pan, then mixture of meat on top of Doritos, then shredded cheese.
Repeat pattern until ingredients are almost all gone.
The last layer should be Doritos, then cheese on top.
Heat in oven for 7 to 9 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: curried snack mix
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, stir together the rice cakes, cereal or crackers and pretzels.
In a cup, stir together the margarine, Worcestershire sauce and curry powder.
Drizzle over cereal mixture.
Toss cereal until coated.
Bake in a 300° oven for 20 minutes, stirring twice.
If desired, store cooled mixture in a tightly covered container.

title: iced cucumber soup
directions: Peel, seed and cut cucumbers in pieces.
Saute onion in margarine until glossy.
Add dill, salt, pepper, cucumbers, soup and water.
Bring to a boil; simmer uncovered 15 minutes.
Run through blender until finely chopped and mixed.
Cool.
Add cream and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain frozen broccoli.
Saute onion in 4 tablespoons margarine.
Stir in flour, add water, cook over low heat until thickened and boils.
Stir in cheese and add to broccoli.
Beat eggs and add.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put remaining 2 tablespoons margarine and cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix well. Cover and chill overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: southern corn
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: no-drip popsicles
directions: Mix Jell-O and Kool-Aid.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix these together until dissolved.
Pour into frames and freeze.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine.
Pour into pan.
Beat together confectioners sugar, softened cream cheese and 2 eggs. Pour over cake mixture.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix well, cutting margarine into flour, and add milk.
Roll out on floured board, cut into biscuits and put on biscuit pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix flour, salt and butter flavored Crisco with pastry blender.
Add water and blend.
Divide into two parts.
Roll out dough, place in pie pan.
Pour cherries in and dot with butter. Cover with other half of rolled out dough.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken gastronomique
directions: Bake chicken for 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.
Mix dressing, preserves and dry soup mix.
Spread over chicken and bake an additional half hour.
Can be kept warm in a 140° oven for another hour if guests are late.
Serves 10.

title: sante fe soup
directions: Cook meat and onion together until meat is browned.
Drain and stir in ranch dressing mix and taco seasoning.
Add remaining ingredients with juices from all.
Add water.
Simmer 2 hours. Add additional water if mixture is too thick.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, peel and slice peaches and lay them in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle white sugar over the peaches.
Layer with a dry cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut and pour melted margarine over all.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° or until it is golden brown.
Can use home canned peaches.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine	all ingredients, except chicken in saucepan and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Place chicken in large baking pan and
pour	barbecue
sauce
over
chicken. Bake, uncovered, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: lamb mustard
directions: Wash leg of lamb.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper for 1 hour before cooking and allow to stand.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and baste leg of lamb throughout cooking.

title: quick no-cook fondant
directions: Blend butter, syrup, salt and vanilla in a large mixing bowl. Add sifted 10x sugar all at once.
Mix all together first with a spoon and then with hands.
Knead in dry ingredients.
Turn onto board and continue kneading until mixture is well blended and smooth.
Store in foil in cool place.
Divide into portions and tint and flavor as desired.
May be shaped into balls and rolled in multi-colored candy, coconut or nuts.
Or fondant may be rolled out and cut in fancy shapes and decorated.
Makes 1 1/3 pounds.

title: quick cookies
directions: Mix and drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes, depending on altitude.

title: macho nacho
directions: Heat chili
and
then
spoon over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat
in
microwave
oven or broil until cheese melts and chips are warm, approximately 1 to 2 minutes.

title: carolers hot chocolate
directions: Measure milk into slow cooker.
Turn on high.
Mix together sugar, salt and cocoa in heavy pan.
Add hot water.
Stir and boil 3 minutes, stirring often.
Pour into milk.
Cook on high 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Yields 12 to 14 (1 cup) servings.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
In large bowl, sprinkle yeast over water.
Gradually add sugar, salt and flour. Knead on floured board 5 to 7 minutes.
Cut dough in half, then cut each half into 6 equal parts.
Roll and stretch into 15-inch ropes.
Shape into pretzels.
Brush with egg and water.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown. Makes 12 pretzels.

title: peanut butter cream cheese pie
directions: Blend peanut butter and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Decorate with whipped cream and drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Let set in freezer for 15 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to instructions on package.
Add margarine; stir until melted.
Add corn and soup; grate 1 cup or more of cheese.
Combine with mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese on top and sprinkle some paprika for color.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together 1 cup powdered sugar and peanut butter like crumbs.
Sprinkle in bottom of crust, pour in pie filling.

title: maple pecan roll
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Boil until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add flavoring.
Cool until thick in pan.
Beat until it loses its gloss.
Pour in buttered plate and cool enough to handle.
Mold into rolls and roll in pecans or chopped salted nuts.

title: fruit and honey spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach, cantaloupe balls and strawberry halves in a large bowl; toss gently.
Combine jam and next 3 ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir with a wire whisk until blended.
Drizzle over spinach mixture and toss well.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: christmastime nog
directions: Put ingredients in punch bowl in the order listed.
Serves 11 to 12 cups.
An open house party hit!

title: cottage cheese fruit salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle in the dry jello. Add pineapple and oranges. Mix together.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: ham macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and bread crumbs.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter.
Stir in bread crumbs. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Combine ingredients and cook until thick.

title: sweet potato corn pone
directions: Put all ingredients into a large bowl and mix well.
Put into a well-greased skillet in oven preheated to 425°.
Bake until the center is done.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Break
cake into small pieces, lay one layer on bottom; mix Cool
Whip, sugar, milk and cheese together;
spread over cake; then add another layer of cake, more mixture.
Then put cherries on top.

title: motorhome beer bread
directions: Grease a bread loaf pan.
Mix all the ingredients together and put into loaf pan.
Let the batter rise if there's time, then cut down center and put in a few thin slices of butter for an extra rich loaf of bread.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cucumber yogurt dressing
directions: Dice cucumber and add other ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour to blend flavor.
Serve over mixed salad greens.

title: potato puffs
directions: Beat eggs well; add potatoes, flour, salt and baking powder. Form balls of this mixture, then fry in hot oil.

title: linguine with summer sauce
directions: Bring tomatoes and garlic to boil in heavy medium saucepan over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and simmer until reduced to 1 1/4 cups, stirring occasionally about 20 minutes.
Season tomato sauce with salt to taste.
Cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender but still firm to bite.
Drain well.
Meanwhile, melt butter in heavy, large saucepan over medium heat.
Mix in basil.
Add pasta; toss to coat.
Add tomatoes to sauce and 3/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese. Toss again.
Season to taste with pepper.
Serve with additional Parmesan.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt cube of butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk.
Makes a crumbly mix; crumble over butter.
Add fruit.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
May take longer than 40 minutes; cook until brown.
Suggested fruits: any kind of berries, peaches, pineapple or apples.

title: crab melt
directions: Melt butter and cheese over low heat. Add lemon juice, worcestershire sauce and garlic salt. Mix well. Process in blender until smooth. In bowl, fold in crabmeat, mix well. Spread onto english muffins. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Cut into quarter pieces. Serve immediately.

title: meat and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles. Rinse in cold water and drain.
Melt butter in frying pan. Add ground beef and cook until browned.
Drain off fat.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder, tomato sauce and paste. Simmer 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine cottage cheese, sour cream, cream cheese and onion.
In buttered casserole, alternate layers of noodles, meat mixture, sour cream mixture and sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: clam and corn chowder with dill
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in hot butter until tender, but not browned.
Stir in flour, dill weed, paprika, salt and Worcestershire.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in drained corn and undrained clams and heat through.
Serve in bowl with cheese and oyster crackers sprinkled on top.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine in casserole dish.
Add 2 cups raw rice.
Put onion soup in a quart pitcher.
Pour bouillon soup in with the onion soup.
Fill the quart pitcher to measure 1 quart with hot or boiling water.
Now pour this liquid mixture (dried onion soup, beef bouillon and hot water that all together measures 1 quart) into the casserole dish that contains the melted margarine and raw rice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil, sealing the edges so the heat doesn't escape.
This is important!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: uncle lynn's baked beans
directions: Wash beans and cover with 6 cups water.
Boil 3 minutes. Cover; let stand 1 hour.
Drain, throw away water.
Put fresh water over beans; add all ingredients and bring to boil.
Transfer to crock immediately.
Cover and place in 300° oven.
Bake 6 to 8 hours.
Uncover last hour to darken beans.
Add hot water if needed.

title: carolyn's broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Batter will be thick.
Put in iron skillet; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: mock angel food cake
directions: Set milk in a pan of water and heat to boiling point. Sift together 3 times the flour, sugar and baking powder. Into this pour the boiling milk and stir until smooth. Then fold in the egg whites and the extract and salt. Pour into ungreased pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: excellent salad
directions: Heat 1 cup of crushed pineapple and 1/4 cup sugar.
Dissolve 1 package lemon gelatin in 1/2 cup water.
Add to above and cool. Whip 1/2 pint whipping cream with 1 small jar pimento cheese. Fold in above and put in the refrigerator until firm.
Then top with 1
package lime gelatin, dissolved in two cups of water.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut stem and core the 4 tomatoes.
Combine other ingredients; mix.
Fill tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry cheese tarts
directions: Line cupcake pans with liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fill liners 2/3 full with cheese mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven; cool.
Top each with a spoonful of pie filling.
Chill.
Yields 24 tarts.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together like pie crust and press in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: irene's chocolate refreshers(makes about 3 dozen bars)
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Combine dates, sugar, butter and water in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until dates soften.
Stir in chocolate bits.
Blend in eggs.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice and milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat the shortening over low heat until melted; remove from heat.
Mix in brown sugar, egg and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inches).
Bake 25 minutes.
Cut into about 2-inch squares while warm.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients gently in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator several hours before serving.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mock blintzes
directions: If you love Cheese Blintzes, these easy Mock Blintzes will also be a hit.
Remove the crusts from bread.
Roll with rolling pin until thin.
Spread generously with softened cream cheese, then roll up.
Dip the rolls in melted butter, then roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven until crispy.
Slice into 1-inch slices.
Good as an appetizer or for brunch or breakfast.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini in a separate bowl.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to zucchini mixture.
Pour into two greased loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked potato slims
directions: Mix oil with water.
Scrub potatoes; cut into 4 to 6 lengthwise wedges each.
Toss a few pieces of potatoes in oil mixture.
Mix Parmesan cheese and Shake 'n Bake together and put into a bag. Shake a few potato wedges at a time until coated well.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Serve with ice cream.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer over medium heat and serve.

title: koblihy(fried doughnuts)
directions: Mix
warm milk, yeast, then add 2 cups flour.
Mix well and let rise to double in size.
Beat yolks, sugar, sour cream and salt.
Add
to
first mixture.
Add 2 3/4 cups flour, mix well and
let
rise
until
double in size.
Place on floured board and
pinch
off
a
tablespoonful at a time.
Fill with cooked poppy seed or prunes.
Be sure to seal each one so they won't leak.
When
they rise a little, deep fry in pot of lard or shortening until golden in color.
Drain in colander or on paper towels.
Then
roll
in
powdered sugar or plain sugar. You can also make plain doughnuts with a hole in the middle.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Mix all vegetables, water, bacon dripping and seasonings in pot.
Simmer on low heat until done.
Stir often.

title: cabbage and bratwurst
directions: In Dutch oven over medium heat, cook bacon, onions and garlic until bacon is crisp, stirring occasionally.
Stir in carrots and cabbage.
Tie cloves and bay leaf in piece of cheesecloth or place in tea ball.
Add to cabbage mixture.
Add bratwurst, partially covering with cabbage mixture.
Pour beef broth and wine over cabbage mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Remove spices. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve with German-style or Dijon mustard and dark bread.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and thinly slice potatoes.
Spray 2-quart casserole with nonstick vegetable spray.
Layer potatoes; sprinkle with onions, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Dot with margarine. Repeat layering with onions and seasonings.
Pour milk over all layers.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine.
Pour margarine into pan to grease pan.
Pour margarine from pan into mixed ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Place ice cream in blender.
Pour in milk and orange juice. Blend at high for 30 seconds.
Add more ice cream for thicker consistency.
Add more orange juice for a thinner drink.

title: corny good chili
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef, onion and celery.
Cook until tender; drain and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in powdered sugar.
Bake at 325°, 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack. Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cherry-pineapple mash(dessert)
directions: In a 9-inch pan, spread 1/2 of cake mix.
Pour 1/2 of melted margarine over cake mix.
Add 1/2 cherry filling, 1/2 of pineapple, 1/2 of coconut and 1/2 of pecans.
Repeat to make a layer.
Cook in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: teriyaki
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces and brown in oil.
Lower heat. Combine sugar, flour and soy sauce and pour over meat.
Add chopped onions and bamboo shoots.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Add bean sprouts, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Serve over rice.
Do not add salt!

title: peach cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs to this mixture. Add vanilla and beat until smooth.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to sugar mixture and beat until smooth. Grease and flour 8-inch square or 9-inch round baking pan.
Place mixture inside.
Place each peach half (open side facing up) around cake mixture.
Fill all batter area with peaches and plum pieces.
Sprinkle fully with sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Place dab of margarine on each piece of fruit.
Bake 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. If inside is damp, leave cake in oven with temperature off.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes down.
Add vegetables (chopped) and seasonings. Cook about 2 hours more.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a double boiler, put milk, rice and salt.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Separate eggs; put whites aside.
Mix egg yolks, sugar, vanilla and half and half.
Stir into rice mixture after 1 hour cooking time.
Cook whole mixture another 1/2 hour and simmer.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Cream sugar and Miracle Whip. Add sifted dry ingredients alternating with water.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: cheerio goodies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil; then set them off. Add and mix well the peanut butter and Cheerios. After mixing well, flatten into buttered pan and cover with chocolate chips and butterscotch chips, which have been melted in a double boiler or microwave.

title: butter squash
directions: Cut butter squash into bite-size chunks.
Steam squash with salt.
Drain and pour squash in baking dish.
Drain pineapple and add to squash.
Slice butter over top.
Sprinkle the brown sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk flapjacks
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
In small bowl or glass measuring cup, combine buttermilk and baking soda. Immediately add buttermilk mixture, eggs and melted butter to flour mixture.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened (mixture should be lumpy).
Lightly oil a griddle or skillet and heat over medium heat.
Spread a heaping 1/2 cup of batter on griddle/skillet to make a 6-inch flapjack.
Cook until bubbles form and begin to break on top surface; turn flapjack over and cook until bottom is golden brown.
Remove flapjack and serve immediately.
Repeat with remaining batter.
Keep finished flapjacks in warm 200° oven while preparing remaining batter.

title: poppy seed rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water. Set aside. Let foam. Sift flour and salt. Cut in butter. Add eggs and blend. Add yeast mixture. Knead on floured board about 5 minutes. Divide into 4 parts. Let rise. Roll out each piece. Spread with Solo poppy seed filling. Roll up and place on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken wing appetizers(makes 36 appetizers)
directions: In small bowl, blend yogurt, steak sauce and honey.
In pie plate, combine cracker crumbs and sesame seed.
Dip chicken pieces in steak sauce mixture, then coat with crumb mixture.
Arrange on greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done, turning after 15 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Add tomatoes and sauce; cook for 30 minutes over medium heat.
Cook macaroni; drain well.
Add to meat mixture; stir well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with cheese over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: fresh apple delight
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, milk, flour and cinnamon in a deep bowl or blender.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish that has been thick coated with butter or oil.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Stir into mixture.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 8 servings.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk good.
Add chocolate milk and crushed candy bars.
Freeze.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in soup pot over medium heat.
Add broccoli and onion.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add flour and mix well.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring well.
Add curry powder, chicken broth and milk; stir well.
Simmer, covered, over low heat 30 minutes.
Cool to room temperature and puree in food processor or blender.
Put back in pot with reserved broccoli tops and reheat over low heat.
Add cream, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot.

title: easy sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion and garlic in a bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Brown in oil in skillet.
Drain meatballs on paper towels.
Reserve pan drippings. Add remaining ingredients to reserved pan drippings, mixing well. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with hot meatballs.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mayonnaise chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Easier than a cake mix!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Crumb buttered bread over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: surprise salad
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: melt in your mouth sugar cookies
directions: Mix together sugars, oil, margarine and eggs.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice by box directions.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Mix both cans of soup with 2 cans of water.
Add chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Mix rice and broccoli.
Put in casserole dish on the bottom.
Pour soup mixture over this. Top with crackers and cheese. Cook until cheese is melted.

title: eggplant casserole(serves 12)
directions: Cook eggplant until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese and crackers.
Mix well.
Alternate layers of eggplant mixture, cheese and cracker crumbs in casserole.
Butter last layer of cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top. Bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Serves 12.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Chop
onion and combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil and then simmer at least one hour.
(Great with hamburgers.)

title: grandma's old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time. Add remaining ingredients.
Knead dough on floured board. Chill 30 to 45 minutes.
Roll out on floured board; cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar/cinnamon.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen large cookies.
Enjoy while hot.

title: savory meat pie
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Combine in 2-quart baking dish lined with pie crust.
Add meat, vegetables and gravy.
Heat at 425° for 15 minutes.
Cover with pie crust.
Cut slits in top for steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple.
Add 1 tablespoon cornstarch to juice; mix well.
Bring to a boil, along with sugar, lemon juice and egg.
Let cool, then add the pineapple, apples, marshmallows and peanuts.
Add Cool Whip and fold all ingredients together. Let set in refrigerator overnight; stir before serving.

title: lemon pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle chops with salt.
Put in shallow baking dish.
On each chop put onion slice, lemon slice, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon ketchup.
Cover and bake 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 30 minutes.
Baste often.

title: traditional leg of lamb(greek name: arni psito)
directions: Wash leg of lamb.
Slit with sharp knife in various places on both sides of lamb.
Thinly slice garlic and insert the slices into slits made in lamb.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brush with melted butter.
Squeeze lemon juice over lamb and place in a roasting pan, fat side up.

title: beef with green pepper, tomato and onion
directions: *If you cannot find it, might find it in Oriental shop.

title: coffee cake
directions: I
add	a
couple
of
teaspoons milk, sprinkle through mixture 3 tablespoons sugar, mixed with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: pecan pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, sugars, corn syrup and flour
in
a
mixing
bowl.
Stir
in
vanilla, pecans and melted margarine.	Spoon mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven
for
minutes
or	until knife inserted into center of filling comes out clean.
Cool and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Crush and add enough crackers to thicken mixture.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle cheese and crackers on top.
Bake for 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: deviled eggs with vegetables
directions: Cut peeled eggs lengthwise into halves.
Slip out yolks.
Mash 2 with fork (save remaining yolks for another purpose).
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Fill whites with yolk mixture, heaping it lightly.
Garnish with pimientos and dill if desired.
Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Makes 4 servings; 2 halves each.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix in blender until smooth.

title: caramel ice cream pie
directions: Combine flour, butter, pecans and brown sugar.
Mix well. Spread on a baking sheet, pressing with fingers to 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Immediately transfer to a large mixing bowl and stir until the mixture is crumbled.
Press crumbs into a 9-inch buttered pie plate, reserving 1/4 cup crumbs. (Crunch crust firms as it freezes.)
Pour 3/4 cup caramel topping into crust.
Freeze.
Spread ice cream evenly over crust; cover and freeze.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of the reserved crumbs over ice cream.
Drizzle remaining caramel topping over pie; sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Freeze until firm.
Let frozen pie stand at room temperature 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.

title: old fashion buckwheat pancakes
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water. Add molasses or honey.
Stir and let stand 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Put flours in a large bowl.
Pour in yeast mixture and enough water to make pancake batter consistency. Cover and let rise overnight.
In the morning, stir in 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and another tablespoon oil. Bake on hot griddle.

title: peach glazed spice cake
directions: Drain peaches, saving 1 cup syrup.
Grease 8-inch round baking dish very well with oil.
Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt directly into oiled dish.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients; add vanilla to one, vinegar to one and 6 tablespoons ??? to one.
Pour reserved peach syrup over all.
Mix with a fork until thoroughly blended.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes. Place peaches on top of cake.
Mix brown sugar, orange rind and cinnamon; sprinkle over peaches.
Dot with butter and broil for 3 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together all but last two ingredients.
Put garlic salt on top then Cheddar cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese with mixture till fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip into mixture.
Divide evenly into 2 pie crusts.
Sprinkle each pie with 1/2 cup chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm.
Can be kept frozen and stored for several weeks.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Hollow out bread loaf.
Break up center section of bread.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Chop dried beef fine.
Add to mixture.

title: strawstack cookies
directions: Melt over hot water the chips and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar and noodles; mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and green pepper.
Add rest of ingredients.
Use large pan or kettle covered.
Cook at medium heat for about an hour or until desired thickness.
Stir occasionally.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly and drain off excess fat.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes (uncovered), stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain and rinse.
Combine the remaining ingredients except the Mozzarella cheese.
Place half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; spread with half the cottage cheese filling.
Add half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Let the lasagna stand for 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done. Mix all ingredients together. Place crumbled crackers on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy garlic rolls
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together butter, cheese, mayonnaise, garlic, parsley and oregano; set aside.
On a lightly floured surface, roll thawed dough into a 14 x 12-inch rectangle (if dough shrinks back after rolling, let rest for a few minutes, then roll again).
Evenly coat dough with butter mixture.
From 12-inch side, roll up dough jelly-roll fashion.
Seal seams.
Divide log of dough into 12 equal slices.
Place slices in a 9-inch round cake pan.
Place slices close together (they can be touching). Let rise in warm area until rolls are almost double in size or until the rolls fill up the pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and done in the center. Remove from oven and pan to cool on a wire rack.

title: florentines
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine heavy cream, butter and sugar in a saucepan.
Stir in all remaining ingredients except melted chocolate.
Drop by tablespoon on greased and floured cookie sheet, about 3-inches apart.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Remove carefully with spatula to cooling rack.
Spiral melted chocolate over cookie tops.
Makes approximately 2 dozen cookies.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Grate the cheese, then mix sausage, cheese and Bisquick together well. Roll into balls (about 1-inch).
Preheat oven to 325°.
Place sausage and cheese balls on ungreased cookie sheet to bake for 30 minutes.

title: lemon spongettes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, salt, lemon juice and rind and beat well.
Add egg yolks and beat until light.
Add milk and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Spoon into Pyrex custard cups and place in pan of cold water.
Bake in slow oven at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 cups.

title: baked pancakes
directions: Mix flour, eggs, lemon juice, milk and nutmeg in bowl.
Melt butter; pour into greased 9-inch square cake pan.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Pour batter into cake pan; bake for 18 to 20 minutes. Serve hot with powdered sugar and jam as a side dish.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix lard in floor with fingers well.
Add salt and baking powder, then milk.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with round cutter.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: stewed hard crabs
directions: Place crabs in large pot. Add water (enough to completely cover crabs). Cut potatoes in quarters; chop onions. Put potatoes and onions over crabs. Add salt, pepper and fat cooked from salt pork. Bring to a boil; cover and cook over medium heat until the potatoes begin to get soft. Add Corn Meal Dumplings around the side of the pot. Cook for about 20 minutes or until gravy begins to thicken.

title: seven seas casserole
directions: Combine the water, soup, onion, lemon juice and salt and let boil.
Pour 1/2 sauce on bottom of casserole dish.
Layer the rice, tuna, Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese (make 2 or 3 layers).
Cover with the rest of the sauce.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry ham rolls
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil.
Stir in cooked rice. Place rice mix on ham slices.
Roll and place, seam side down, in oiled roasting pan.
Repeat.
Melt cranberry sauce.
Add brown sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over ham rolls.
Bake at 350° until hot through.

title: nan's spareribs
directions: Bake spareribs until brown.
In saucepan, combine water, soy sauce and sugar and cook on medium until it begins to thicken. Reduce heat and add each sparerib until coated.
Serve immediately or keep warm.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Cool to room temperature.
Whip cream.
Add both liqueurs to marshmallow mixture.
Fold in heavy cream.
Pour into pie crust.
Put morsels on top with cherry and freeze.

title: potato almond patties
directions: Heat water, milk, salt and margarine to boiling in 2-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat, stir in potatoes and onions; whip with fork until thick, cool.
Shape potatoes into 6 patties, each about 3 inches in diameter.
Mix almonds and flour and coat each patty with almond mixture.
To serve, heat margarine and oil in skillet until hot.
Cook patties until brown, turning once or can refrigerate for 48 hours until ready to serve.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar until thick and foamy.
Add zucchini and pineapple.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into first mixture, just until blended.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Makes two loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix the cream cheese and butter together.
Fold in shrimp, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Roll into a ball using plastic wrap or wax paper.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Spread on crackers and serve.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift the flour with soda, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and allspice; sift into vanilla, eggs, sugar, oil, buttermilk and prunes.
Mix and add nuts.
Bake in an iron skillet at 275° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
This is especially good on a fall evening served warm.

title: veggie salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, green pepper, green beans, peas and corn alternately.
Top with mayonnaise and crumbled bacon.
Chill and mix before serving.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Place in mixer and using a dough hook, add the remaining ingredients.
Turn out on floured board and knead for 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves, brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: orange pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Let cool.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix with hand and shape into balls (walnut size).
Roll into 1 egg white, beaten with fork in a separate bowl.
Then roll in crushed walnuts in separate bowl.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press each cookie with thumb (deep).
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes on bottom rack.
Remove and fill with 1/2 teaspoon fruit preserves (blueberry, apricot, strawberry and cherry work well). Place back in oven on top rack for 10 minutes.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well with hands. Form as near into shape of a ball as possible, then place in freezer overnight or for several hours. Then remove and re-form in shape of a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, then add sherbet and Cool Whip and stir until melted (mixture will be thick).
Add remaining ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Pour into a 2-quart mold.
Refrigerate 8 to 10 hours before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer chips and pour in meat mixture.
Spread 8 or 10 ounces grated Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Place in 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Top with thin slices of butter or margarine. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.
Approximate time: 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan chocolate pound cake
directions: Combine butter and shortening, mixing well.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix well after each addition.
(I beat the tar out of it!)
Pour batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan. Sprinkle and mash pecans down into batter.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove from pan and let cake cool completely.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook, mash and drain squash.
Pour melted oleo over stuffing; save some for the top.
Mix everything together.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with stuffing that was put aside.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, butter and bananas.
Sift flour, then add to banana mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: icebox vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large glass bowl; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Cool slightly and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
May be stored in covered container in refrigerator for up to 1 week.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine until smooth and soft. Cream in both brown sugar and granulated sugar and the egg.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix until smooth. Add rolled oats.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on flat surface. Yields 2 dozen.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Add shortening, sour milk and vanilla. Beat hard for 2 minutes by hand or with an electric mixer on medium speed.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake top springs back to the touch.

title: fried squash
directions: Wash and slice squash.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dip in corn meal.
Fry in hot cooking oil until brown and tender.
(Green tomatoes are good cooked this way.)

title: morning glorious muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
In another bowl, combine carrot, apple, coconut, dates and pecans.
Stir in beaten eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Grease muffin pans or line with paper bake cups.
Spoon batter into pans.
Bake in a 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
Remove from pans; cool on wire racks.
Package muffins for giving as desired.
Makes about 24.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in warm-hot applesauce.
Add pineapple, 7-Up and nuts.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan and chill.
Serve over lettuce.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and process until ice is chopped fine.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 cups.

title: fruit punch
directions: Add all ingredients except lime sherbet.
Float sherbet in punch bowl.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Firmly press into loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tofu dip for vegetables
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend thoroughly.

title: oyster rockerfeller casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 9 x 13 casserole.
Drain oysters and arrange in single layer on bottom of dish.
Melt butter and saute celery and onion until soft.
Add parsley, spinach, aniseed, Worcestershire, bread crumbs, salt, and pepper. Spread this mixture over oysters and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove and if necessary, pour off water.
Sprinkle with cheese and a very thin layer of bread crumbs and bake another 10 minutes or until browned.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat in large bowl with electric mixer for 3 minutes, until well blended.
Bake in Bundt or angel food cake pan in 350° oven for 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: crisp sweet pickle slices
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Add sliced onions, garlic and the peppers, cut in narrow strips.
Add salt; cover with cracked ice and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Seal in sterilized jars.
Process 5 minutes in hot water bath. Makes 8 pints.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Stir jello into boiling water.
Add softened cream cheese (may use mixer to blend well).
Add pineapple, nuts, cherries and Coke. Mix all well.
Chill for several hours.

title: taco dip (heated)
directions: Brown hamburger and onions and drain.
Melt cheese and add chili and taco sauce.
Serve warm with taco chips.

title: strawberry lime cooler
directions: In a blender, at high speed, blend strawberries, seltzer, lime syrup, lime juice and ice cubes until mixture is smooth.
Pour mixture into chilled glasses.
Makes 4 drinks.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Mix all the ingredients and place on cookie sheet.
Roast at 300° for 10 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally until nuts are coated.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients; form into a loaf.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain off fat.
Mix 3/4 cup catsup and 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
Put on top of loaf and put back in oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Grease bottoms of 2 loaf pans.
Mix rhubarb, pears, sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, jello and water; cook until clear.
Let cool.
Place strawberries in pie shell.
Pour cooled mixture over strawberries.
Chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: whipped strawberry delight
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup of liquid.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in juice and water.
Chill until thick and syrupy.
Whip gelatin until fluffy.
Fold in Cool-Whip, add pineapple and nuts.
Pour into lightly oiled 5 cup mold or 9 x 13 pan.
Chill until set.

title: yeast raised waffles
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in bowl and blend in egg yolks. Beat whites and cream of tartar in another bowl until stiff, but not dry.
Fold 1/4 whites into batter.
Fold in remaining whites.

title: chicken salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a food processor and process until completely blended.
Chill 1 hour; serve as is with crackers or in scooped out tomatoes on a bed of lettuce.

title: crab stew
directions: In large pot,
add
milk
and evaporated milk.
Cook on medium-low heat.
Do
not
boil.
In another pan, melt butter. Add soups and crab meat.
Cook until hot and bubbly.
Add crab mixture to milk.
After
all
is
heated
together, thicken to desired consistency with
flour
and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
If you prefer spicy stew, add a dash of Tabasco.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium heat and saute the onions, green onions, bell pepper and parsley until the onions are clear.
Stirring, add the tomato sauce and garlic, then the rice, salt, sausage and enough water to cover the rice by about 1-inch.
Cook until most of the juice is gone.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 1 hour; don't lift the lid for at least 45 minutes.
This makes a red jambalaya.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip, Jello and cottage cheese and mix well. Add drained pineapple, coconut and chopped pecans. Mix real good and let cool in ice box until ready to serve.

title: sugar beans
directions: Save some bacon strips for decorating top, if desired.

title: microwave blueberry muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add blueberries.
Add milk, melted butter and egg.
Mix until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Do not overbeat.
Spoon batter into paper-lined microwaveproof baking or cupcake pan.
Don't fill more than 2/3 up.
Microwave at Med-High power for 3 minutes.
Let rest for 3 minutes.
Microwave at High power for another 2 to 3 minutes or until muffins are done.
They will still be a little soft in the center.
Let them rest in the pan for a couple of minutes.
Serve them warm with butter or honey.

title: uncle al's chili recipe
directions: Brown the beef until cooked and drain off grease.
Saute onions, green peppers and garlic in butter; drain and add to beef. Saute bacon until crisp and drain off fat.
Crumble and add to beef with jalapeno peppers, chili powder, red pepper, cayenne pepper, salt and oregano.
Stir in water, tomato paste and barbecue sauce; bring to a boil.
Simmer for one hour.
Stir in beans.
Cover and continue simmering for 30 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Strain juice from oysters and save.
Remove shells from oysters, if there are any.	Put 1/4 cup of butter in frypan on medium heat, add oysters and cook until oysters are curled and cooked.
Pour
in
strained juice, milk and 1/4 cup butter and salt and
pepper to taste; heat to boiling point.
Reduce heat to medium;
add
cooked
oysters.
Simmer for 2 minutes, then serve at once.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Make hole in flour, add beaten eggs and 1 cup broth.
Mix and roll on floured surface.
Cut into strips, drop into boiling broth until tender.

title: popa's soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat seasoned with salt, pepper, onion, garlic and celery salt with 1/2 cup chopped onion and 1/2 cup green pepper.
Cook potatoes and carrots together 15 minutes, then add hamburger meat.
Add corn, English peas, tomato soup and diced tomatoes.
Let come to boil; turn low to simmer.
Serve with Mexican corn bread.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in eggs and vanilla; sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in half of flour mixture into sugar mixture.
Beat in 2 tablespoons hot water.
Beat in remaining flour and then remaining water.
Stir in apples and nuts. Spread into 2 greased 9-inch square pans and bake at 350° about 50 minutes.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until clear and tender (about 10 minutes).
In a casserole dish, layer half of the onions and butter mixture, one half crackers and half of the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Serve over rice with cornbread.
Serves 6.

title: never-fail caramel pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and boil for 2 minutes.
Add soda; bring to boil.
Mix together the rest of ingredients and add the first mixture.
Cook until thick.
Simple and good.
You can cut sugar down to 1 cup and is good, but not as sweet.

title: montana fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla and nuts in saucepan; bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Let cool; add vanilla and beat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add nuts.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put chicken in a dish.
Mix soups, broth, salt and pepper; pour over chicken.
Mix 1 cup of milk and 1 cup of Bisquick.
Pour this over all.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "come on over cake"
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush crackers.
Mix with nuts and baking powder.
Beat whites with sugar and vanilla.
Fold cracker mixture into whites and bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix Dream Whip according to package.
Add cream cheese, powdered sugar and drained pineapple.
Spread over crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: beef steak - potato scallop
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut meat into 1-inch cubes; coat with flour.
Brown meat in melted shortening in a skillet.
Add onions; cook and stir until tender.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with 3 tablespoons flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Pour water over mixture.
Cover; bake 45 to 60 minutes or until meat is tender.
Turn oven up to 450°.
Arrange potatoes on meat.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Bake uncovered about 30 minutes longer.

title: hungarian cucumber salad
directions: Several hours before serving, slice the cucumbers as thin as you possibly can.
Place them in a glass bowl.
